8087 void CEulerSolver::BC_NonReflecting(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container,
8088  CNumerics *conv_numerics, CNumerics *visc_numerics, CConfig *config, unsigned short val_marker) {
8089  unsigned short iDim, iVar, jVar, kVar;
8090  unsigned long iVertex, iPoint, Point_Normal;
8091  su2double Area, UnitNormal[3];
8092 
8093  su2double *Velocity_b, Velocity2_b, Enthalpy_b, Energy_b, StaticEnergy_b, Density_b, Kappa_b, Chi_b, Pressure_b, Temperature_b;
8094  su2double *Velocity_i, Velocity2_i, Enthalpy_i, Energy_i, StaticEnergy_i, Density_i, Kappa_i, Chi_i, Pressure_i, SoundSpeed_i;
8095  su2double Pressure_e;
8096  su2double ProjVelocity_i;
8097  su2double **P_Tensor, **invP_Tensor, *Lambda_i, **Jacobian_b, **DubDu, *dw, *u_b;
8098  su2double *gridVel;
8099  su2double *V_boundary, *V_domain, *S_boundary, *S_domain;
8100 
8101  bool implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme_Flow() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
8102  bool grid_movement = config->GetGrid_Movement();
8103  string Marker_Tag = config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(val_marker);
8104  bool viscous = config->GetViscous();
8105  su2double *Normal;
8106 
8107  Normal = new su2double[nDim];
8108 
8109  Velocity_i = new su2double[nDim];
8110  Velocity_b = new su2double[nDim];
8111 
8112 
8113  Lambda_i = new su2double[nVar];
8114 
8115  u_b = new su2double[nVar];
8116  dw = new su2double[nVar];
8117 
8118  S_boundary = new su2double[8];
8119 
8120  P_Tensor = new su2double*[nVar];
8121  invP_Tensor = new su2double*[nVar];
8122  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
8123  {
8124  P_Tensor[iVar] = new su2double[nVar];
8125  invP_Tensor[iVar] = new su2double[nVar];
8126  }
8127 
8128  /*--- new declarations ---*/
8129  std::vector<std::complex<su2double> > c4k ;// std::complex<su2double> c3k[nVertex-OddEven]=0;
8130  std::vector<std::complex<su2double> > c2k ;// std::complex<su2double> c3k[nVertex-OddEven]=0;
8131  std::vector<std::complex<su2double> > c3k ;// std::complex<su2double> c3k[nVertex-OddEven]=0;
8132 
8133  su2double deltaDensity, deltaPressure, AvgMach, deltaTangVelocity, deltaNormalVelocity, cc,rhoc,c1j,c2j,c3j,c4j,
8134  avg_c1, avg_c2, avg_c3, avg_c4,TangVelocity, NormalVelocity, GilesBeta, c4js, dc4js, *delta_c, **R_Matrix, *deltaprim;
8135 
8136 
8137  delta_c = new su2double[nVar];
8138  deltaprim = new su2double[nVar];
8139  R_Matrix= new su2double*[nVar];
8140  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
8141  {
8142  R_Matrix[iVar] = new su2double[nVar];
8143  }
8144 
8145 
8146  Mixing_Process(geometry, solver_container, config, val_marker);
8147 
8148  cc = AveragedSoundSpeed[val_marker]*AveragedSoundSpeed[val_marker];
8149  rhoc = AveragedSoundSpeed[val_marker]*AveragedDensity[val_marker];
8150  AvgMach = AveragedMach[val_marker];
8151 
8152  conv_numerics->GetRMatrix(AveragedSoundSpeed[val_marker], AveragedDensity[val_marker], AveragedNormal[val_marker], R_Matrix);
8153 
8154  // Boundary_Fourier(geometry, solver_container, config, val_marker, c4k, nboundaryvertex);
8155  // Boundary_Fourier(geometry, solver_container, config, val_marker, c2k,c3k,nboundaryvertex);
8156 
8157  /*--- Loop over all the vertices on this boundary marker ---*/
8158 
8159  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[val_marker]; iVertex++) {
8160 
8161  V_boundary= GetCharacPrimVar(val_marker, iVertex);
8162 
8163  iPoint = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNode();
8164 
8165  /*--- Check if the node belongs to the domain (i.e., not a halo node) ---*/
8166  if (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain()) {
8167 
8168  /*--- Index of the closest interior node ---*/
8169  Point_Normal = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal_Neighbor();
8170 
8171  /*--- Normal vector for this vertex (negate for outward convention) ---*/
8172  geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Normal);
8173  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Normal[iDim] = -Normal[iDim];
8174  conv_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
8175 
8176  Area = 0.0;
8177  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Area += Normal[iDim]*Normal[iDim];
8178  Area = sqrt (Area);
8179 
8180  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8181  UnitNormal[iDim] = Normal[iDim]/Area;
8182 
8183  /*--- Retrieve solution at this boundary node ---*/
8184  V_domain = node[iPoint]->GetPrimitive();
8185 
8186  /*--- Compute the internal state u_i ---*/
8187  Velocity2_i = 0;
8188  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8189  {
8190  Velocity_i[iDim] = node[iPoint]->GetVelocity(iDim);
8191  Velocity2_i += Velocity_i[iDim]*Velocity_i[iDim];
8192  }
8193 
8194 
8195  Density_i = node[iPoint]->GetDensity();
8196 
8197  Energy_i = node[iPoint]->GetEnergy();
8198  StaticEnergy_i = Energy_i - 0.5*Velocity2_i;
8199 
8200  FluidModel->SetTDState_rhoe(Density_i, StaticEnergy_i);
8201 
8202  Pressure_i = FluidModel->GetPressure();
8203  Enthalpy_i = Energy_i + Pressure_i/Density_i;
8204 
8205  SoundSpeed_i = FluidModel->GetSoundSpeed();
8206 
8207  Kappa_i = FluidModel->GetdPde_rho() / Density_i;
8208  Chi_i = FluidModel->GetdPdrho_e() - Kappa_i * StaticEnergy_i;
8209 
8210  ProjVelocity_i = 0.0;
8211  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8212  ProjVelocity_i += Velocity_i[iDim]*UnitNormal[iDim];
8213 
8214 
8215  switch(config->GetKind_Data_NRBC(Marker_Tag))
8216  {
8217 
8218  //TODO(turbo), generilize for 3D case
8219  //TODO(turbo), generilize for Inlet and Outlet in for backflow treatment
8220  //TODO(turbo), implement not uniform inlet and radial equilibrium for the outlet
8221 
8222  case MIXING_IN:
8223 
8224  /* --- Compute jump of primitive variable --- */
8225  deltaDensity = ExtAveragedDensity[val_marker] - AveragedDensity[val_marker];
8226  deltaPressure = ExtAveragedPressure[val_marker] - AveragedPressure[val_marker];
8227  NormalVelocity= UnitNormal[0]*Velocity_i[0] + UnitNormal[1]*Velocity_i[1];
8228  deltaTangVelocity= ExtAveragedTangVelocity[val_marker]+AveragedTangVelocity[val_marker];
8229  deltaNormalVelocity= ExtAveragedNormalVelocity[val_marker]+AveragedNormalVelocity[val_marker];
8230 
8231  /* --- Compute characteristic jumps --- */
8232  avg_c1= -cc*deltaDensity +deltaPressure;
8233  avg_c2= (rhoc*deltaTangVelocity);
8234  avg_c3= (rhoc*deltaNormalVelocity +deltaPressure);
8235  c4j= -rhoc*(-NormalVelocity +AveragedNormalVelocity[val_marker]) +(Pressure_i - AveragedPressure[val_marker]);
8236 
8237  /* --- Impose Inlet BC --- */
8238  delta_c[0] = avg_c1;
8239  delta_c[1] = avg_c2;
8240  delta_c[2] = avg_c3;
8241  delta_c[3] = c4j;
8242  break;
8243 
8244  case MIXING_OUT:
8245 
8246  /* --- Compute jump of primitive variable --- */
8247  deltaDensity = Density_i - AveragedDensity[val_marker];
8248  deltaPressure = Pressure_i - AveragedPressure[val_marker];
8249  TangVelocity= UnitNormal[0]*Velocity_i[1] - UnitNormal[1]*Velocity_i[0];
8250  NormalVelocity= UnitNormal[0]*Velocity_i[0] + UnitNormal[1]*Velocity_i[1];
8251  deltaTangVelocity= TangVelocity - AveragedTangVelocity[val_marker];
8252  deltaNormalVelocity= NormalVelocity - AveragedNormalVelocity[val_marker];
8253 
8254  /* --- Compute characteristic jumps --- */
8255  c1j= -cc*deltaDensity +deltaPressure;
8256  c2j= rhoc*deltaTangVelocity;
8257  c3j= rhoc*deltaNormalVelocity + deltaPressure;
8258  avg_c4 = rhoc*(AveragedNormalVelocity[val_marker]+ExtAveragedNormalVelocity[val_marker]) -(AveragedPressure[val_marker]-ExtAveragedPressure[val_marker]);
8259 
8260  /* --- implementation of supersonic NRBC ---*/
8261  if (AvgMach > 1.001){
8262  if (AveragedTangVelocity[val_marker] >= 0.0){
8263  GilesBeta= -sqrt(pow(AvgMach,2)-1.0);
8264  }else{
8265  GilesBeta= sqrt(pow(AvgMach,2)-1.0);
8266  }
8267  c4js= (2.0 * AveragedNormalMach[val_marker])/(GilesBeta - AveragedTangMach[val_marker])*c2j - (GilesBeta+AveragedTangMach[val_marker])/(GilesBeta-AveragedTangMach[val_marker])*c3j;
8268  dc4js = c4js;
8269  }else{
8270  dc4js = 0.0;
8271  }
8272 
8273  /* --- Impose Outlet BC --- */
8274  delta_c[0] = c1j;
8275  delta_c[1] = c2j;
8276  delta_c[2] = c3j;
8277  delta_c[3] = avg_c4 + dc4js;
8278  break;
8279 
8280  case STATIC_PRESSURE:
8281 
8282  Pressure_e = config->GetNRBC_Var1(Marker_Tag);
8283  Pressure_e /= config->GetPressure_Ref();
8284 
8285  /* --- Compute jump of primitive variable --- */
8286  deltaDensity = Density_i - AveragedDensity[val_marker];
8287  deltaPressure = Pressure_i - AveragedPressure[val_marker];
8288  TangVelocity= UnitNormal[0]*Velocity_i[1] - UnitNormal[1]*Velocity_i[0];
8289  NormalVelocity= UnitNormal[0]*Velocity_i[0] + UnitNormal[1]*Velocity_i[1];
8290  deltaTangVelocity= TangVelocity - AveragedTangVelocity[val_marker];
8291  deltaNormalVelocity= NormalVelocity - AveragedNormalVelocity[val_marker];
8292 
8293  /* --- Compute characteristic jumps --- */
8294  c1j= -cc*deltaDensity +deltaPressure;
8295  c2j= rhoc*deltaTangVelocity;
8296  c3j=rhoc*deltaNormalVelocity + deltaPressure;
8297  c4j=-rhoc*deltaNormalVelocity + deltaPressure;
8298  avg_c4 = -2.0*(AveragedPressure[val_marker]-Pressure_e);
8299 
8300  /* --- implementation of supersonic NRBC ---*/
8301  if (AvgMach > 1.001){
8302  if (AveragedTangVelocity[val_marker] >= 0.0){
8303  GilesBeta= -sqrt(pow(AvgMach,2)-1.0);
8304  }else{
8305  GilesBeta= sqrt(pow(AvgMach,2)-1.0);
8306  }
8307  c4js= (2.0 * AveragedNormalMach[val_marker])/(GilesBeta - AveragedTangMach[val_marker])*c2j - (GilesBeta+AveragedTangMach[val_marker])/(GilesBeta-AveragedTangMach[val_marker])*c3j;
8308  dc4js = c4js;
8309  }else{
8310  dc4js = 0.0;
8311  }
8312 
8313  /* --- Impose Outlet BC --- */
8314  delta_c[0] = c1j;
8315  delta_c[1] = c2j;
8316  delta_c[2] = c3j;
8317  delta_c[3] = avg_c4 + dc4js;
8318  break;
8319 
8320  default:
8321  cout << "Warning! Invalid NRBC input!" << endl;
8322  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
8323  break;
8324 
8325  }
8326 
8327  /*--- Compute primitive jump from characteristic variables ---*/
8328  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
8329  {
8330  deltaprim[iVar]=0;
8331  for (jVar = 0; jVar < nVar; jVar++)
8332  {
8333  deltaprim[iVar] += R_Matrix[iVar][jVar]*delta_c[jVar];
8334  }
8335  }
8336 
8337  /*--- Compute P (matrix of right eigenvectors) ---*/
8338  conv_numerics->GetPMatrix(&Density_i, Velocity_i, &SoundSpeed_i, &Enthalpy_i, &Chi_i, &Kappa_i, UnitNormal, P_Tensor);
8339 
8340  /*--- Compute inverse P (matrix of left eigenvectors)---*/
8341  conv_numerics->GetPMatrix_inv(invP_Tensor, &Density_i, Velocity_i, &SoundSpeed_i, &Chi_i, &Kappa_i, UnitNormal);
8342 
8343  /*--- eigenvalues contribution due to grid motion ---*/
8344  if (grid_movement){
8345  gridVel = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel();
8346  su2double ProjGridVel = 0.0;
8347  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8348  ProjGridVel += gridVel[iDim]*UnitNormal[iDim];
8349  ProjVelocity_i -= ProjGridVel;
8350  }
8351 
8352  /*--- Flow eigenvalues ---*/
8353  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8354  Lambda_i[iDim] = ProjVelocity_i;
8355  Lambda_i[nVar-2] = ProjVelocity_i + SoundSpeed_i;
8356  Lambda_i[nVar-1] = ProjVelocity_i - SoundSpeed_i;
8357 
8358  //TODO(turbo), provide the under relaxation factor sigma from cfg file
8359  su2double sigma;
8360  sigma = 1.0;
8361 
8362  /*--- retrieve boundary variables ---*/
8363  Density_b = AveragedDensity[val_marker] + sigma*deltaprim[0];
8364  Pressure_b = AveragedPressure[val_marker] + sigma*deltaprim[3];
8365  switch(config->GetKind_Data_NRBC(Marker_Tag)){
8366  case MIXING_IN:
8367  NormalVelocity = AveragedNormalVelocity[val_marker] - sigma*deltaprim[1];
8368  TangVelocity = AveragedTangVelocity[val_marker] - sigma*deltaprim[2];
8369  break;
8370  case MIXING_OUT: case STATIC_PRESSURE:
8371  NormalVelocity = AveragedNormalVelocity[val_marker] + sigma*deltaprim[1];
8372  TangVelocity = AveragedTangVelocity[val_marker] + sigma*deltaprim[2];
8373  break;
8374  default:
8375  cout << "Warning! Invalid NRBC input!" << endl;
8376  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
8377  break;
8378  }
8379 
8380  Velocity_b[0] = NormalVelocity*UnitNormal[0] - TangVelocity*UnitNormal[1];
8381  Velocity_b[1] = NormalVelocity*UnitNormal[1] + TangVelocity*UnitNormal[0];
8382  Velocity2_b = 0.0;
8383  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
8384  Velocity2_b+= Velocity_b[iDim]*Velocity_b[iDim];
8385  }
8386 
8387  FluidModel->SetTDState_Prho(Pressure_b, Density_b);
8388  Energy_b = FluidModel->GetStaticEnergy() + 0.5*Velocity2_b;
8389  StaticEnergy_b = FluidModel->GetStaticEnergy();
8390  Temperature_b= FluidModel->GetTemperature();
8391  Enthalpy_b = Energy_b + Pressure_b/Density_b;
8392  Kappa_b = FluidModel->GetdPde_rho() / Density_b;
8393  Chi_b = FluidModel->GetdPdrho_e() - Kappa_b * StaticEnergy_b;
8394 
8395  /*--- Compute the thermodynamic state in u_b ---*/
8396  u_b[0]=Density_b;
8397  u_b[1]=Density_b*Velocity_b[0];
8398  u_b[2]=Density_b*Velocity_b[1];
8399  u_b[3]=Energy_b*Density_b;
8400 
8401  /*--- Compute the residuals ---*/
8402  conv_numerics->GetInviscidProjFlux(&Density_b, Velocity_b, &Pressure_b, &Enthalpy_b, Normal, Residual);
8403 
8404  /*--- Residual contribution due to grid motion ---*/
8405  if (grid_movement) {
8406  gridVel = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel();
8407  su2double projVelocity = 0.0;
8408  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8409  projVelocity += gridVel[iDim]*Normal[iDim];
8410  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
8411  Residual[iVar] -= projVelocity *(u_b[iVar]);
8412  }
8413 
8414  if (implicit) {
8415  /*--- Residual contribution due to grid motion ---*/
8416  Jacobian_b = new su2double*[nVar];
8417  DubDu = new su2double*[nVar];
8418  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
8419  {
8420  Jacobian_b[iVar] = new su2double[nVar];
8421  DubDu[iVar] = new su2double[nVar];
8422  }
8423 
8424  /*--- Initialize DubDu to unit matrix---*/
8425  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
8426  {
8427  for (jVar = 0; jVar < nVar; jVar++)
8428  DubDu[iVar][jVar]= 0;
8429 
8430  DubDu[iVar][iVar]= 1;
8431  }
8432 
8433  /*--- Compute DubDu -= RNL---*/
8434  for (iVar=0; iVar<nVar; iVar++)
8435  {
8436  for (jVar=0; jVar<nVar; jVar++)
8437  {
8438  for (kVar=0; kVar<nVar; kVar++)
8439  {
8440  if (Lambda_i[kVar]<0)
8441  DubDu[iVar][jVar] -= P_Tensor[iVar][kVar] * invP_Tensor[kVar][jVar];
8442  }
8443  }
8444  }
8445 
8446  /*--- Compute flux Jacobian in state b ---*/
8447  conv_numerics->GetInviscidProjJac(Velocity_b, &Enthalpy_b, &Chi_b, &Kappa_b, Normal, 1.0, Jacobian_b);
8448 
8449  /*--- Jacobian contribution due to grid motion ---*/
8450  if (grid_movement)
8451  {
8452  su2double projVelocity = 0.0;
8453  gridVel = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel();
8454  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8455  projVelocity += gridVel[iDim]*Normal[iDim];
8456  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++){
8457  Residual[iVar] -= projVelocity *(u_b[iVar]);
8458  Jacobian_b[iVar][iVar] -= projVelocity;
8459  }
8460 
8461  }
8462 
8463  /*--- initiate Jacobian_i to zero matrix ---*/
8464  for (iVar=0; iVar<nVar; iVar++)
8465  for (jVar=0; jVar<nVar; jVar++)
8466  Jacobian_i[iVar][jVar] = 0.0;
8467  /*--- Compute numerical flux Jacobian at node i ---*/
8468 
8469  for (iVar=0; iVar<nVar; iVar++) {
8470  for (jVar=0; jVar<nVar; jVar++) {
8471  for (kVar=0; kVar<nVar; kVar++) {
8472  Jacobian_i[iVar][jVar] += Jacobian_b[iVar][kVar] * DubDu[kVar][jVar];
8473  }
8474  }
8475 
8476  }
8477 
8478  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
8479  delete [] Jacobian_b[iVar];
8480  delete [] DubDu[iVar];
8481  }
8482  delete [] Jacobian_b;
8483  delete [] DubDu;
8484  }
8485 
8486  /*--- Update residual value ---*/
8487  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
8488 
8489  /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
8490  if (implicit)
8491  Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
8492 
8493  /*--- Roe Turkel preconditioning, set the value of beta ---*/
8494  if (config->GetKind_Upwind() == TURKEL)
8495  node[iPoint]->SetPreconditioner_Beta(conv_numerics->GetPrecond_Beta());
8496 
8497  /*--- Viscous contribution ---*/
8498  if (viscous) {
8499 
8500  /*--- Primitive variables, using the derived quantities ---*/
8501  V_boundary[0] = Temperature_b;
8502  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8503  V_boundary[iDim+1] = Velocity_b[iDim];
8504  V_boundary[nDim+1] = Pressure_b;
8505  V_boundary[nDim+2] = Density_b;
8506  V_boundary[nDim+3] = Enthalpy_b;
8507 
8508  /*--- Set laminar and eddy viscosity at the infinity ---*/
8509  V_boundary[nDim+5] = FluidModel->GetLaminarViscosity();
8510  V_boundary[nDim+6] = node[iPoint]->GetEddyViscosity();
8511  V_boundary[nDim+7] = FluidModel->GetThermalConductivity();
8512  V_boundary[nDim+8] = FluidModel->GetCp();
8513 
8514  /*--- Set the normal vector and the coordinates ---*/
8515  visc_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
8516  visc_numerics->SetCoord(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(), geometry->node[Point_Normal]->GetCoord());
8517 
8518  /*--- Primitive variables, and gradient ---*/
8519  visc_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_boundary);
8520  visc_numerics->SetPrimVarGradient(node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive(), node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive());
8521 
8522  /*--- Secondary variables ---*/
8523  S_domain = node[iPoint]->GetSecondary();
8524 
8525  /*--- Compute secondary thermodynamic properties (partial derivatives...) ---*/
8526 
8527  S_boundary[0]= FluidModel->GetdPdrho_e();
8528  S_boundary[1]= FluidModel->GetdPde_rho();
8529 
8530  S_boundary[2]= FluidModel->GetdTdrho_e();
8531  S_boundary[3]= FluidModel->GetdTde_rho();
8532 
8533  /*--- Compute secondary thermo-physical properties (partial derivatives...) ---*/
8534 
8535  S_boundary[4]= FluidModel->Getdmudrho_T();
8536  S_boundary[5]= FluidModel->GetdmudT_rho();
8537 
8538  S_boundary[6]= FluidModel->Getdktdrho_T();
8539  S_boundary[7]= FluidModel->GetdktdT_rho();
8540 
8541  visc_numerics->SetSecondary(S_domain, S_boundary);
8542 
8543  /*--- Turbulent kinetic energy ---*/
8544  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST)
8545  visc_numerics->SetTurbKineticEnergy(solver_container[TURB_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0), solver_container[TURB_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0));
8546 
8547  /*--- Compute and update residual ---*/
8548  visc_numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
8549  LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(iPoint, Residual);
8550 
8551  /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
8552  if (implicit)
8553  Jacobian.SubtractBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
8554 
8555  }
8556 
8557  }
8558  }
8559 
8560  /*--- Free locally allocated memory ---*/
8561  delete [] Normal;
8562 
8563  delete [] Velocity_b;
8564  delete [] Velocity_i;
8565 
8566  delete [] S_boundary;
8567  delete [] Lambda_i;
8568  delete [] u_b;
8569  delete [] dw;
8570 
8571 
8572  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
8573  {
8574  delete [] P_Tensor[iVar];
8575  delete [] invP_Tensor[iVar];
8576  }
8577  delete [] P_Tensor;
8578  delete [] invP_Tensor;
8579 
8580 
8581  delete [] delta_c;
8582  delete [] deltaprim;
8583  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
8584  {
8585  delete [] R_Matrix[iVar];
8586  }
8587  delete [] R_Matrix;
8588 
8589 
8590 }
8591 
8592 void CEulerSolver::BC_Inlet(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container,
8593  CNumerics *conv_numerics, CNumerics *visc_numerics, CConfig *config, unsigned short val_marker) {
8594  unsigned short iDim;
8595  unsigned long iVertex, iPoint, Point_Normal;
8596  su2double P_Total, T_Total, Velocity[3], Velocity2, H_Total, Temperature, Riemann,
8597  Pressure, Density, Energy, *Flow_Dir, Mach2, SoundSpeed2, SoundSpeed_Total2, Vel_Mag,
8598  alpha, aa, bb, cc, dd, Area, UnitNormal[3];
8599  su2double *V_inlet, *V_domain;
8600 
8601  bool implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme_Flow() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
8602  bool grid_movement = config->GetGrid_Movement();
8603  bool compressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == COMPRESSIBLE);
8604  bool incompressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == INCOMPRESSIBLE);
8605  bool freesurface = (config->GetKind_Regime() == FREESURFACE);
8606  su2double Two_Gamma_M1 = 2.0/Gamma_Minus_One;
8607  su2double Gas_Constant = config->GetGas_ConstantND();
8608  unsigned short Kind_Inlet = config->GetKind_Inlet();
8609  string Marker_Tag = config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(val_marker);
8610  bool viscous = config->GetViscous();
8611  bool gravity = (config->GetGravityForce());
8612  bool tkeNeeded = (((config->GetKind_Solver() == RANS )|| (config->GetKind_Solver() == DISC_ADJ_RANS)) &&
8613  (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST));
8614  su2double *Normal = new su2double[nDim];
8615 
8616  /*--- Loop over all the vertices on this boundary marker ---*/
8617 
8618  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[val_marker]; iVertex++) {
8619 
8620  /*--- Allocate the value at the inlet ---*/
8621 
8622  V_inlet = GetCharacPrimVar(val_marker, iVertex);
8623 
8624  iPoint = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNode();
8625 
8626  /*--- Check if the node belongs to the domain (i.e., not a halo node) ---*/
8627 
8628  if (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain()) {
8629 
8630  /*--- Index of the closest interior node ---*/
8631 
8632  Point_Normal = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal_Neighbor();
8633 
8634  /*--- Normal vector for this vertex (negate for outward convention) ---*/
8635 
8636  geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Normal);
8637  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Normal[iDim] = -Normal[iDim];
8638  conv_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
8639 
8640  Area = 0.0;
8641  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Area += Normal[iDim]*Normal[iDim];
8642  Area = sqrt (Area);
8643 
8644  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8645  UnitNormal[iDim] = Normal[iDim]/Area;
8646 
8647  /*--- Retrieve solution at this boundary node ---*/
8648 
8649  V_domain = node[iPoint]->GetPrimitive();
8650 
8651  /*--- Build the fictitious intlet state based on characteristics ---*/
8652 
8653  if (compressible) {
8654 
8655  /*--- Subsonic inflow: there is one outgoing characteristic (u-c),
8656  therefore we can specify all but one state variable at the inlet.
8657  The outgoing Riemann invariant provides the final piece of info.
8658  Adapted from an original implementation in the Stanford University
8659  multi-block (SUmb) solver in the routine bcSubsonicInflow.f90
8660  written by Edwin van der Weide, last modified 04-20-2009. ---*/
8661 
8662  switch (Kind_Inlet) {
8663 
8664  /*--- Total properties have been specified at the inlet. ---*/
8665 
8666  case TOTAL_CONDITIONS:
8667 
8668  /*--- Retrieve the specified total conditions for this inlet. ---*/
8669 
8670  if (gravity) P_Total = config->GetInlet_Ptotal(Marker_Tag) - geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(nDim-1)*STANDART_GRAVITY;
8671  else P_Total = config->GetInlet_Ptotal(Marker_Tag);
8672  T_Total = config->GetInlet_Ttotal(Marker_Tag);
8673  Flow_Dir = config->GetInlet_FlowDir(Marker_Tag);
8674 
8675  /*--- Non-dim. the inputs if necessary. ---*/
8676 
8677  P_Total /= config->GetPressure_Ref();
8678  T_Total /= config->GetTemperature_Ref();
8679 
8680  /*--- Store primitives and set some variables for clarity. ---*/
8681 
8682  Density = V_domain[nDim+2];
8683  Velocity2 = 0.0;
8684  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
8685  Velocity[iDim] = V_domain[iDim+1];
8686  Velocity2 += Velocity[iDim]*Velocity[iDim];
8687  }
8688  Energy = V_domain[nDim+3] - V_domain[nDim+1]/V_domain[nDim+2];
8689  Pressure = V_domain[nDim+1];
8690  H_Total = (Gamma*Gas_Constant/Gamma_Minus_One)*T_Total;
8691  SoundSpeed2 = Gamma*Pressure/Density;
8692 
8693  /*--- Compute the acoustic Riemann invariant that is extrapolated
8694  from the domain interior. ---*/
8695 
8696  Riemann = 2.0*sqrt(SoundSpeed2)/Gamma_Minus_One;
8697  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8698  Riemann += Velocity[iDim]*UnitNormal[iDim];
8699 
8700  /*--- Total speed of sound ---*/
8701 
8702  SoundSpeed_Total2 = Gamma_Minus_One*(H_Total - (Energy + Pressure/Density)+0.5*Velocity2) + SoundSpeed2;
8703 
8704  /*--- Dot product of normal and flow direction. This should
8705  be negative due to outward facing boundary normal convention. ---*/
8706 
8707  alpha = 0.0;
8708  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8709  alpha += UnitNormal[iDim]*Flow_Dir[iDim];
8710 
8711  /*--- Coefficients in the quadratic equation for the velocity ---*/
8712 
8713  aa = 1.0 + 0.5*Gamma_Minus_One*alpha*alpha;
8714  bb = -1.0*Gamma_Minus_One*alpha*Riemann;
8715  cc = 0.5*Gamma_Minus_One*Riemann*Riemann
8716  -2.0*SoundSpeed_Total2/Gamma_Minus_One;
8717 
8718  /*--- Solve quadratic equation for velocity magnitude. Value must
8719  be positive, so the choice of root is clear. ---*/
8720 
8721  dd = bb*bb - 4.0*aa*cc;
8722  dd = sqrt(max(0.0, dd));
8723  Vel_Mag = (-bb + dd)/(2.0*aa);
8724  Vel_Mag = max(0.0, Vel_Mag);
8725  Velocity2 = Vel_Mag*Vel_Mag;
8726 
8727  /*--- Compute speed of sound from total speed of sound eqn. ---*/
8728 
8729  SoundSpeed2 = SoundSpeed_Total2 - 0.5*Gamma_Minus_One*Velocity2;
8730 
8731  /*--- Mach squared (cut between 0-1), use to adapt velocity ---*/
8732 
8733  Mach2 = Velocity2/SoundSpeed2;
8734  Mach2 = min(1.0, Mach2);
8735  Velocity2 = Mach2*SoundSpeed2;
8736  Vel_Mag = sqrt(Velocity2);
8737  SoundSpeed2 = SoundSpeed_Total2 - 0.5*Gamma_Minus_One*Velocity2;
8738 
8739  /*--- Compute new velocity vector at the inlet ---*/
8740 
8741  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8742  Velocity[iDim] = Vel_Mag*Flow_Dir[iDim];
8743 
8744  /*--- Static temperature from the speed of sound relation ---*/
8745 
8746  Temperature = SoundSpeed2/(Gamma*Gas_Constant);
8747 
8748  /*--- Static pressure using isentropic relation at a point ---*/
8749 
8750  Pressure = P_Total*pow((Temperature/T_Total), Gamma/Gamma_Minus_One);
8751 
8752  /*--- Density at the inlet from the gas law ---*/
8753 
8754  Density = Pressure/(Gas_Constant*Temperature);
8755 
8756  /*--- Using pressure, density, & velocity, compute the energy ---*/
8757 
8758  Energy = Pressure/(Density*Gamma_Minus_One) + 0.5*Velocity2;
8759  if (tkeNeeded) Energy += GetTke_Inf();
8760 
8761  /*--- Primitive variables, using the derived quantities ---*/
8762 
8763  V_inlet[0] = Temperature;
8764  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8765  V_inlet[iDim+1] = Velocity[iDim];
8766  V_inlet[nDim+1] = Pressure;
8767  V_inlet[nDim+2] = Density;
8768  V_inlet[nDim+3] = Energy + Pressure/Density;
8769 
8770  break;
8771 
8772  /*--- Mass flow has been specified at the inlet. ---*/
8773 
8774  case MASS_FLOW:
8775 
8776  /*--- Retrieve the specified mass flow for the inlet. ---*/
8777 
8778  Density = config->GetInlet_Ttotal(Marker_Tag);
8779  Vel_Mag = config->GetInlet_Ptotal(Marker_Tag);
8780  Flow_Dir = config->GetInlet_FlowDir(Marker_Tag);
8781 
8782  /*--- Non-dim. the inputs if necessary. ---*/
8783 
8784  Density /= config->GetDensity_Ref();
8785  Vel_Mag /= config->GetVelocity_Ref();
8786 
8787  /*--- Get primitives from current inlet state. ---*/
8788 
8789  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8790  Velocity[iDim] = node[iPoint]->GetVelocity(iDim);
8791  Pressure = node[iPoint]->GetPressure();
8792  SoundSpeed2 = Gamma*Pressure/V_domain[nDim+2];
8793 
8794  /*--- Compute the acoustic Riemann invariant that is extrapolated
8795  from the domain interior. ---*/
8796 
8797  Riemann = Two_Gamma_M1*sqrt(SoundSpeed2);
8798  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8799  Riemann += Velocity[iDim]*UnitNormal[iDim];
8800 
8801  /*--- Speed of sound squared for fictitious inlet state ---*/
8802 
8803  SoundSpeed2 = Riemann;
8804  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8805  SoundSpeed2 -= Vel_Mag*Flow_Dir[iDim]*UnitNormal[iDim];
8806 
8807  SoundSpeed2 = max(0.0,0.5*Gamma_Minus_One*SoundSpeed2);
8808  SoundSpeed2 = SoundSpeed2*SoundSpeed2;
8809 
8810  /*--- Pressure for the fictitious inlet state ---*/
8811 
8812  Pressure = SoundSpeed2*Density/Gamma;
8813 
8814  /*--- Energy for the fictitious inlet state ---*/
8815 
8816  Energy = Pressure/(Density*Gamma_Minus_One) + 0.5*Vel_Mag*Vel_Mag;
8817  if (tkeNeeded) Energy += GetTke_Inf();
8818 
8819  /*--- Primitive variables, using the derived quantities ---*/
8820 
8821  V_inlet[0] = Pressure / ( Gas_Constant * Density);
8822  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8823  V_inlet[iDim+1] = Vel_Mag*Flow_Dir[iDim];
8824  V_inlet[nDim+1] = Pressure;
8825  V_inlet[nDim+2] = Density;
8826  V_inlet[nDim+3] = Energy + Pressure/Density;
8827 
8828  break;
8829  }
8830  }
8831  if (incompressible) {
8832 
8833  /*--- Retrieve the specified velocity for the inlet. ---*/
8834 
8835  Vel_Mag = config->GetInlet_Ptotal(Marker_Tag)/config->GetVelocity_Ref();
8836  Flow_Dir = config->GetInlet_FlowDir(Marker_Tag);
8837 
8838  /*--- Store the velocity in the primitive variable vector ---*/
8839 
8840  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
8841  V_inlet[iDim+1] = Vel_Mag*Flow_Dir[iDim];
8842 
8843  /*--- Neumann condition for pressure ---*/
8844 
8845  V_inlet[0] = node[iPoint]->GetPressureInc();
8846 
8847  /*--- Constant value of density ---*/
8848 
8849  V_inlet[nDim+1] = GetDensity_Inf();
8850 
8851  /*--- Beta coefficient from the config file ---*/
8852 
8853  V_inlet[nDim+2] = config->GetArtComp_Factor();
8854 
8855  }
8856  if (freesurface) {
8857 
8858  /*--- Neumann condition for pressure, density, level set, and distance ---*/
8859 
8860  V_inlet[0] = node[iPoint]->GetPressureInc();
8861  V_inlet[nDim+1] = node[iPoint]->GetDensityInc();
8862  V_inlet[nDim+5] = node[iPoint]->GetLevelSet();
8863  V_inlet[nDim+6] = node[iPoint]->GetDistance();
8864 
8865  /*--- The velocity is computed from the infinity values ---*/
8866 
8867  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
8868  V_inlet[iDim+1] = GetVelocity_Inf(iDim);
8869  }
8870 
8871  /*--- The y/z velocity is interpolated due to the
8872  free surface effect on the pressure ---*/
8873 
8874  V_inlet[nDim] = node[iPoint]->GetPrimitive(nDim);
8875 
8876  /*--- Neumann condition for artifical compresibility factor ---*/
8877 
8878  V_inlet[nDim+2] = config->GetArtComp_Factor();
8879 
8880  }
8881 
8882  /*--- Set various quantities in the solver class ---*/
8883 
8884  conv_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_inlet);
8885 
8886  if (grid_movement)
8887  conv_numerics->SetGridVel(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel(), geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel());
8888 
8889  /*--- Compute the residual using an upwind scheme ---*/
8890 
8891  conv_numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
8892 
8893  /*--- Update residual value ---*/
8894 
8895  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
8896 
8897  /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
8898 
8899  if (implicit)
8900  Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
8901 
8902  /*--- Roe Turkel preconditioning, set the value of beta ---*/
8903 
8904  if (config->GetKind_Upwind() == TURKEL)
8905  node[iPoint]->SetPreconditioner_Beta(conv_numerics->GetPrecond_Beta());
8906 
8907  /*--- Viscous contribution ---*/
8908 
8909  if (viscous) {
8910 
8911  /*--- Set laminar and eddy viscosity at the infinity ---*/
8912 
8913  if (compressible) {
8914  V_inlet[nDim+5] = node[iPoint]->GetLaminarViscosity();
8915  V_inlet[nDim+6] = node[iPoint]->GetEddyViscosity();
8916  }
8917  if (incompressible || freesurface) {
8918  V_inlet[nDim+3] = node[iPoint]->GetLaminarViscosityInc();
8919  V_inlet[nDim+4] = node[iPoint]->GetEddyViscosityInc();
8920  }
8921 
8922  /*--- Set the normal vector and the coordinates ---*/
8923 
8924  visc_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
8925  visc_numerics->SetCoord(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(), geometry->node[Point_Normal]->GetCoord());
8926 
8927  /*--- Primitive variables, and gradient ---*/
8928 
8929  visc_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_inlet);
8930  visc_numerics->SetPrimVarGradient(node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive(), node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive());
8931 
8932  /*--- Turbulent kinetic energy ---*/
8933 
8934  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST)
8935  visc_numerics->SetTurbKineticEnergy(solver_container[TURB_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0), solver_container[TURB_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0));
8936 
8937  /*--- Compute and update residual ---*/
8938 
8939  visc_numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
8940  LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(iPoint, Residual);
8941 
8942  /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
8943 
8944  if (implicit)
8945  Jacobian.SubtractBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
8946 
8947  }
8948 
8949  }
8950  }
8951 
8952  /*--- Free locally allocated memory ---*/
8953 
8954  delete [] Normal;
8955 
8956 }
8957 
8958 void CEulerSolver::BC_Outlet(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container,
8959  CNumerics *conv_numerics, CNumerics *visc_numerics, CConfig *config, unsigned short val_marker) {
8960  unsigned short iVar, iDim;
8961  unsigned long iVertex, iPoint, Point_Normal;
8962  su2double LevelSet, Density_Outlet = 0.0, Pressure, P_Exit, Velocity[3],
8963  Velocity2, Entropy, Density, Energy, Riemann, Vn, SoundSpeed, Mach_Exit, Vn_Exit,
8964  Area, UnitNormal[3], Height, yCoordRef, yCoord;
8965  su2double *V_outlet, *V_domain;
8966 
8967  bool implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme_Flow() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
8968  su2double Gas_Constant = config->GetGas_ConstantND();
8969  bool compressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == COMPRESSIBLE);
8970  bool incompressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == INCOMPRESSIBLE);
8971  bool freesurface = (config->GetKind_Regime() == FREESURFACE);
8972  bool grid_movement = config->GetGrid_Movement();
8973  su2double FreeSurface_Zero = config->GetFreeSurface_Zero();
8974  su2double epsilon = config->GetFreeSurface_Thickness();
8975  su2double RatioDensity = config->GetRatioDensity();
8976  string Marker_Tag = config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(val_marker);
8977  bool viscous = config->GetViscous();
8978  bool gravity = (config->GetGravityForce());
8979  su2double PressFreeSurface = GetPressure_Inf();
8980  su2double Froude = config->GetFroude();
8981  bool tkeNeeded = (((config->GetKind_Solver() == RANS )|| (config->GetKind_Solver() == DISC_ADJ_RANS)) &&
8982  (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST));
8983  su2double *Normal = new su2double[nDim];
8984 
8985  /*--- Loop over all the vertices on this boundary marker ---*/
8986  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[val_marker]; iVertex++) {
8987 
8988  /*--- Allocate the value at the outlet ---*/
8989  V_outlet = GetCharacPrimVar(val_marker, iVertex);
8990 
8991  iPoint = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNode();
8992 
8993  /*--- Check if the node belongs to the domain (i.e., not a halo node) ---*/
8994  if (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain()) {
8995 
8996  /*--- Index of the closest interior node ---*/
8997  Point_Normal = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal_Neighbor();
8998 
8999  /*--- Normal vector for this vertex (negate for outward convention) ---*/
9000  geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Normal);
9001  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Normal[iDim] = -Normal[iDim];
9002  conv_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
9003 
9004  Area = 0.0;
9005  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Area += Normal[iDim]*Normal[iDim];
9006  Area = sqrt (Area);
9007 
9008  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9009  UnitNormal[iDim] = Normal[iDim]/Area;
9010 
9011  /*--- Current solution at this boundary node ---*/
9012  V_domain = node[iPoint]->GetPrimitive();
9013 
9014  /*--- Build the fictitious intlet state based on characteristics ---*/
9015  if (compressible) {
9016 
9017  /*--- Retrieve the specified back pressure for this outlet. ---*/
9018  if (gravity) P_Exit = config->GetOutlet_Pressure(Marker_Tag) - geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(nDim-1)*STANDART_GRAVITY;
9019  else P_Exit = config->GetOutlet_Pressure(Marker_Tag);
9020 
9021  /*--- Non-dim. the inputs if necessary. ---*/
9022  P_Exit = P_Exit/config->GetPressure_Ref();
9023 
9024  /*--- Check whether the flow is supersonic at the exit. The type
9025  of boundary update depends on this. ---*/
9026  Density = V_domain[nDim+2];
9027  Velocity2 = 0.0; Vn = 0.0;
9028  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
9029  Velocity[iDim] = V_domain[iDim+1];
9030  Velocity2 += Velocity[iDim]*Velocity[iDim];
9031  Vn += Velocity[iDim]*UnitNormal[iDim];
9032  }
9033  Pressure = V_domain[nDim+1];
9034  SoundSpeed = sqrt(Gamma*Pressure/Density);
9035  Mach_Exit = sqrt(Velocity2)/SoundSpeed;
9036 
9037  if (Mach_Exit >= 1.0) {
9038 
9039  /*--- Supersonic exit flow: there are no incoming characteristics,
9040  so no boundary condition is necessary. Set outlet state to current
9041  state so that upwinding handles the direction of propagation. ---*/
9042  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nPrimVar; iVar++) V_outlet[iVar] = V_domain[iVar];
9043 
9044  } else {
9045 
9046  /*--- Subsonic exit flow: there is one incoming characteristic,
9047  therefore one variable can be specified (back pressure) and is used
9048  to update the conservative variables. Compute the entropy and the
9049  acoustic Riemann variable. These invariants, as well as the
9050  tangential velocity components, are extrapolated. Adapted from an
9051  original implementation in the Stanford University multi-block
9052  (SUmb) solver in the routine bcSubsonicOutflow.f90 by Edwin van
9053  der Weide, last modified 09-10-2007. ---*/
9054 
9055  Entropy = Pressure*pow(1.0/Density, Gamma);
9056  Riemann = Vn + 2.0*SoundSpeed/Gamma_Minus_One;
9057 
9058  /*--- Compute the new fictious state at the outlet ---*/
9059  Density = pow(P_Exit/Entropy,1.0/Gamma);
9060  Pressure = P_Exit;
9061  SoundSpeed = sqrt(Gamma*P_Exit/Density);
9062  Vn_Exit = Riemann - 2.0*SoundSpeed/Gamma_Minus_One;
9063  Velocity2 = 0.0;
9064  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
9065  Velocity[iDim] = Velocity[iDim] + (Vn_Exit-Vn)*UnitNormal[iDim];
9066  Velocity2 += Velocity[iDim]*Velocity[iDim];
9067  }
9068  Energy = P_Exit/(Density*Gamma_Minus_One) + 0.5*Velocity2;
9069  if (tkeNeeded) Energy += GetTke_Inf();
9070 
9071  /*--- Conservative variables, using the derived quantities ---*/
9072  V_outlet[0] = Pressure / ( Gas_Constant * Density);
9073  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9074  V_outlet[iDim+1] = Velocity[iDim];
9075  V_outlet[nDim+1] = Pressure;
9076  V_outlet[nDim+2] = Density;
9077  V_outlet[nDim+3] = Energy + Pressure/Density;
9078 
9079  }
9080  }
9081  if (incompressible) {
9082 
9083  /*--- The pressure is computed from the infinity values ---*/
9084  if (gravity) {
9085  yCoordRef = 0.0;
9086  yCoord = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(nDim-1);
9087  V_outlet[0] = GetPressure_Inf() + GetDensity_Inf()*((yCoordRef-yCoord)/(config->GetFroude()*config->GetFroude()));
9088  }
9089  else {
9090  V_outlet[0] = GetPressure_Inf();
9091  }
9092 
9093  /*--- Neumann condition for the velocity ---*/
9094  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
9095  V_outlet[iDim+1] = node[Point_Normal]->GetPrimitive(iDim+1);
9096  }
9097 
9098  /*--- Constant value of density ---*/
9099  V_outlet[nDim+1] = GetDensity_Inf();
9100 
9101  /*--- Beta coefficient from the config file ---*/
9102  V_outlet[nDim+2] = config->GetArtComp_Factor();
9103 
9104  }
9105  if (freesurface) {
9106 
9107  /*--- Imposed pressure, density, level set and distance ---*/
9108  Height = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(nDim-1);
9109  LevelSet = Height - FreeSurface_Zero;
9110  if (LevelSet < -epsilon) Density_Outlet = config->GetDensity_FreeStreamND();
9111  if (LevelSet > epsilon) Density_Outlet = RatioDensity*config->GetDensity_FreeStreamND();
9112  V_outlet[0] = PressFreeSurface + Density_Outlet*((FreeSurface_Zero-Height)/(Froude*Froude));
9113  V_outlet[nDim+1] = Density_Outlet;
9114  V_outlet[nDim+5] = LevelSet;
9115  V_outlet[nDim+6] = LevelSet;
9116 
9117  /*--- Neumann condition in the interface for the pressure, density and level set and distance ---*/
9118  if (fabs(LevelSet) <= epsilon) {
9119  V_outlet[0] = node[Point_Normal]->GetPressureInc();
9120  V_outlet[nDim+1] = node[Point_Normal]->GetDensityInc();
9121  V_outlet[nDim+5] = node[Point_Normal]->GetLevelSet();
9122  V_outlet[nDim+6] = node[Point_Normal]->GetDistance();
9123  }
9124 
9125  /*--- Neumann condition for the velocity ---*/
9126  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
9127  V_outlet[iDim+1] = node[Point_Normal]->GetPrimitive(iDim+1);
9128  }
9129 
9130  /*--- Neumann condition for artifical compresibility factor ---*/
9131  V_outlet[nDim+2] = config->GetArtComp_Factor();
9132 
9133  }
9134 
9135  /*--- Set various quantities in the solver class ---*/
9136  conv_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_outlet);
9137 
9138  if (grid_movement)
9139  conv_numerics->SetGridVel(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel(), geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel());
9140 
9141  /*--- Compute the residual using an upwind scheme ---*/
9142  conv_numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
9143 
9144  /*--- Update residual value ---*/
9145  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
9146 
9147  /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
9148  if (implicit) {
9149  Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
9150  }
9151 
9152  /*--- Roe Turkel preconditioning, set the value of beta ---*/
9153  if (config->GetKind_Upwind() == TURKEL)
9154  node[iPoint]->SetPreconditioner_Beta(conv_numerics->GetPrecond_Beta());
9155 
9156  /*--- Viscous contribution ---*/
9157  if (viscous) {
9158 
9159  /*--- Set laminar and eddy viscosity at the infinity ---*/
9160  if (compressible) {
9161  V_outlet[nDim+5] = node[iPoint]->GetLaminarViscosity();
9162  V_outlet[nDim+6] = node[iPoint]->GetEddyViscosity();
9163  }
9164  if (incompressible || freesurface) {
9165  V_outlet[nDim+3] = node[iPoint]->GetLaminarViscosityInc();
9166  V_outlet[nDim+4] = node[iPoint]->GetEddyViscosityInc();
9167  }
9168 
9169  /*--- Set the normal vector and the coordinates ---*/
9170  visc_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
9171  visc_numerics->SetCoord(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(), geometry->node[Point_Normal]->GetCoord());
9172 
9173  /*--- Primitive variables, and gradient ---*/
9174  visc_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_outlet);
9175  visc_numerics->SetPrimVarGradient(node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive(), node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive());
9176 
9177  /*--- Turbulent kinetic energy ---*/
9178  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST)
9179  visc_numerics->SetTurbKineticEnergy(solver_container[TURB_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0), solver_container[TURB_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0));
9180 
9181  /*--- Compute and update residual ---*/
9182  visc_numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
9183  LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(iPoint, Residual);
9184 
9185  /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
9186  if (implicit)
9187  Jacobian.SubtractBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
9188 
9189  }
9190 
9191  }
9192  }
9193 
9194  /*--- Free locally allocated memory ---*/
9195  delete [] Normal;
9196 
9197 }
9198 
9199 void CEulerSolver::BC_Supersonic_Inlet(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container,
9200  CNumerics *conv_numerics, CNumerics *visc_numerics, CConfig *config, unsigned short val_marker) {
9201  unsigned short iDim;
9202  unsigned long iVertex, iPoint, Point_Normal;
9203  su2double *V_inlet, *V_domain;
9204 
9205  su2double Density, Pressure, Temperature, Energy, *Velocity, Velocity2;
9206  su2double Gas_Constant = config->GetGas_ConstantND();
9207 
9208  bool implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme_Flow() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
9209  bool grid_movement = config->GetGrid_Movement();
9210  bool viscous = config->GetViscous();
9211  string Marker_Tag = config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(val_marker);
9212  bool tkeNeeded = (((config->GetKind_Solver() == RANS )|| (config->GetKind_Solver() == DISC_ADJ_RANS)) &&
9213  (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST));
9214  su2double *Normal = new su2double[nDim];
9215 
9216  /*--- Supersonic inlet flow: there are no outgoing characteristics,
9217  so all flow variables can be imposed at the inlet.
9218  First, retrieve the specified values for the primitive variables. ---*/
9219 
9220  Temperature = config->GetInlet_Temperature(Marker_Tag);
9221  Pressure = config->GetInlet_Pressure(Marker_Tag);
9222  Velocity = config->GetInlet_Velocity(Marker_Tag);
9223 
9224  /*--- Density at the inlet from the gas law ---*/
9225 
9226  Density = Pressure/(Gas_Constant*Temperature);
9227 
9228  /*--- Non-dim. the inputs if necessary. ---*/
9229 
9230  Temperature = Temperature/config->GetTemperature_Ref();
9231  Pressure = Pressure/config->GetPressure_Ref();
9232  Density = Density/config->GetDensity_Ref();
9233  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9234  Velocity[iDim] = Velocity[iDim]/config->GetVelocity_Ref();
9235 
9236  /*--- Compute the energy from the specified state ---*/
9237 
9238  Velocity2 = 0.0;
9239  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9240  Velocity2 += Velocity[iDim]*Velocity[iDim];
9241  Energy = Pressure/(Density*Gamma_Minus_One)+0.5*Velocity2;
9242  if (tkeNeeded) Energy += GetTke_Inf();
9243 
9244  /*--- Loop over all the vertices on this boundary marker ---*/
9245 
9246  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[val_marker]; iVertex++) {
9247 
9248  /*--- Allocate the value at the outlet ---*/
9249 
9250  V_inlet = GetCharacPrimVar(val_marker, iVertex);
9251 
9252  /*--- Primitive variables, using the derived quantities ---*/
9253 
9254  V_inlet[0] = Temperature;
9255  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9256  V_inlet[iDim+1] = Velocity[iDim];
9257  V_inlet[nDim+1] = Pressure;
9258  V_inlet[nDim+2] = Density;
9259  V_inlet[nDim+3] = Energy + Pressure/Density;
9260 
9261  iPoint = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNode();
9262 
9263  /*--- Check if the node belongs to the domain (i.e, not a halo node) ---*/
9264 
9265  if (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain()) {
9266 
9267  /*--- Index of the closest interior node ---*/
9268 
9269  Point_Normal = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal_Neighbor();
9270 
9271  /*--- Current solution at this boundary node ---*/
9272 
9273  V_domain = node[iPoint]->GetPrimitive();
9274 
9275  /*--- Normal vector for this vertex (negate for outward convention) ---*/
9276 
9277  geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Normal);
9278  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Normal[iDim] = -Normal[iDim];
9279 
9280  /*--- Set various quantities in the solver class ---*/
9281 
9282  conv_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
9283  conv_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_inlet);
9284 
9285  if (grid_movement)
9286  conv_numerics->SetGridVel(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel(),
9287  geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel());
9288 
9289  /*--- Compute the residual using an upwind scheme ---*/
9290 
9291  conv_numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
9292  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
9293 
9294  /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
9295 
9296  if (implicit)
9297  Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
9298 
9299  /*--- Viscous contribution ---*/
9300 
9301  if (viscous) {
9302 
9303  /*--- Set laminar and eddy viscosity at the infinity ---*/
9304 
9305  V_inlet[nDim+5] = node[iPoint]->GetLaminarViscosity();
9306  V_inlet[nDim+6] = node[iPoint]->GetEddyViscosity();
9307 
9308  /*--- Set the normal vector and the coordinates ---*/
9309 
9310  visc_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
9311  visc_numerics->SetCoord(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(), geometry->node[Point_Normal]->GetCoord());
9312 
9313  /*--- Primitive variables, and gradient ---*/
9314 
9315  visc_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_inlet);
9316  visc_numerics->SetPrimVarGradient(node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive(), node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive());
9317 
9318  /*--- Turbulent kinetic energy ---*/
9319 
9320  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST)
9321  visc_numerics->SetTurbKineticEnergy(solver_container[TURB_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0), solver_container[TURB_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0));
9322 
9323  /*--- Compute and update residual ---*/
9324 
9325  visc_numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
9326  LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(iPoint, Residual);
9327 
9328  /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
9329 
9330  if (implicit)
9331  Jacobian.SubtractBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
9332  }
9333 
9334  }
9335  }
9336 
9337  /*--- Free locally allocated memory ---*/
9338 
9339  delete [] Normal;
9340 
9341 }

9343 void CEulerSolver::BC_Supersonic_Outlet(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container,
9344  CNumerics *conv_numerics, CNumerics *visc_numerics, CConfig *config, unsigned short val_marker) {
9345  unsigned short iDim;
9346  unsigned long iVertex, iPoint, Point_Normal;
9347  su2double *V_outlet, *V_domain;
9348 
9349  bool implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme_Flow() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
9350  bool grid_movement = config->GetGrid_Movement();
9351  bool viscous = config->GetViscous();
9352  string Marker_Tag = config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(val_marker);
9353 
9354  su2double *Normal = new su2double[nDim];
9355 
9356  /*--- Supersonic outlet flow: there are no ingoing characteristics,
9357  so all flow variables can should be interpolated from the domain. ---*/
9358 
9359  /*--- Loop over all the vertices on this boundary marker ---*/
9360 
9361  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[val_marker]; iVertex++) {
9362 
9363  iPoint = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNode();
9364 
9365  /*--- Check if the node belongs to the domain (i.e, not a halo node) ---*/
9366 
9367  if (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain()) {
9368 
9369  /*--- Index of the closest interior node ---*/
9370 
9371  Point_Normal = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal_Neighbor();
9372

9374 
9375  V_domain = node[iPoint]->GetPrimitive();

9378 
9379  V_outlet = GetCharacPrimVar(val_marker, iVertex);
9380

9384  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9385  V_outlet[iDim+1] = V_domain[iDim+1];
9386  V_outlet[nDim+1] = V_domain[nDim+1];
9387  V_outlet[nDim+2] = V_domain[nDim+2];
9388  V_outlet[nDim+3] = V_domain[nDim+3];
9389

9391 
9392  V_domain = node[iPoint]->GetPrimitive();
9393 
9394  /*--- Normal vector for this vertex (negate for outward convention) ---*/
9395 
9396  geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Normal);
9397  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Normal[iDim] = -Normal[iDim];
9398 
9399  /*--- Set various quantities in the solver class ---*/
9400 
9401  conv_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
9402  conv_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_outlet);
9403 
9404  if (grid_movement)
9405  conv_numerics->SetGridVel(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel(),
9406  geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel());
9407

9409 
9410  conv_numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
9411  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
9412 
9413  /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
9414 
9415  if (implicit)
9416  Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
9417 
9418  /*--- Viscous contribution ---*/
9419 
9420  if (viscous) {
9421 
9422  /*--- Set laminar and eddy viscosity at the infinity ---*/
9423 
9424  V_outlet[nDim+5] = node[iPoint]->GetLaminarViscosity();
9425  V_outlet[nDim+6] = node[iPoint]->GetEddyViscosity();
9426 
9427  /*--- Set the normal vector and the coordinates ---*/
9428 
9429  visc_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
9430  visc_numerics->SetCoord(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(), geometry->node[Point_Normal]->GetCoord());
9431 
9432  /*--- Primitive variables, and gradient ---*/
9433 
9434  visc_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_outlet);
9435  visc_numerics->SetPrimVarGradient(node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive(), node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive());
9436 
9437  /*--- Turbulent kinetic energy ---*/
9438 
9439  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST)
9440  visc_numerics->SetTurbKineticEnergy(solver_container[TURB_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0), solver_container[TURB_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0));
9441

9443

9445  LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(iPoint, Residual);
9446 
9447  /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
9448 
9449  if (implicit)
9450  Jacobian.SubtractBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
9451  }
9452 
9453  }

9461 
9462 void CEulerSolver::BC_Engine_Inflow(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container, CNumerics *conv_numerics, CNumerics *visc_numerics, CConfig *config, unsigned short val_marker) {
9463 
9464  unsigned short iDim;
9465  unsigned long iVertex, iPoint, Point_Normal;
9466  su2double Pressure, Inflow_Pressure, Velocity[3], Velocity2, Entropy, Target_Inflow_Mach = 0.0, Density, Energy,
9467  Riemann, Area, UnitNormal[3], Vn, SoundSpeed, Vn_Exit, Inflow_Pressure_inc, Inflow_Pressure_old, Inflow_Mach_old;
9468  su2double *V_inflow, *V_domain;
9469 
9470  su2double DampingFactor = config->GetDamp_Engine_Inflow();
9471  bool implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme_Flow() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
9472  bool viscous = config->GetViscous();
9473  su2double Gas_Constant = config->GetGas_ConstantND();
9474  string Marker_Tag = config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(val_marker);
9475  bool tkeNeeded = (((config->GetKind_Solver() == RANS )|| (config->GetKind_Solver() == DISC_ADJ_RANS)) &&
9476  (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST));
9477  su2double Baseline_Press = 0.75 * config->GetPressure_FreeStreamND();
9478 
9479  su2double *Normal = new su2double[nDim];
9480 
9481  /*--- Retrieve the specified target fan face mach in the nacelle. ---*/
9482 
9483  Target_Inflow_Mach = config->GetInflow_Mach_Target(Marker_Tag);
9484 
9485  /*--- Retrieve the old fan face pressure and mach number in the nacelle (this has been computed in a preprocessing). ---*/
9486 
9487  Inflow_Pressure_old = config->GetInflow_Pressure(Marker_Tag); // Note that has been computed by the code (non-dimensional).
9488  Inflow_Mach_old = config->GetInflow_Mach(Marker_Tag);
9489 
9490  /*--- Compute the pressure increment (note that increasing pressure decreases flow speed) ---*/
9491 
9492  Inflow_Pressure_inc = - (1.0 - (Inflow_Mach_old/Target_Inflow_Mach)) * Baseline_Press;
9493 
9494  /*--- Estimate the new fan face pressure ---*/
9495 
9496  Inflow_Pressure = (1.0 - DampingFactor)*Inflow_Pressure_old + DampingFactor * (Inflow_Pressure_old + Inflow_Pressure_inc);
9497 
9498  /*--- Loop over all the vertices on this boundary marker ---*/
9499 
9500  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[val_marker]; iVertex++) {
9501 
9502  /*--- Allocate the value at the outlet ---*/
9503 
9504  V_inflow = GetCharacPrimVar(val_marker, iVertex);
9505 
9506  iPoint = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNode();
9507 
9508  /*--- Check if the node belongs to the domain (i.e, not a halo node) ---*/
9509 
9510  if (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain()) {
9511 
9512  /*--- Index of the closest interior node ---*/
9513 
9514  Point_Normal = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal_Neighbor();
9515 
9516  /*--- Normal vector for this vertex (negate for outward convention) ---*/
9517 
9518  geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Normal);
9519  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Normal[iDim] = -Normal[iDim];
9520 
9521  Area = 0.0;
9522  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9523  Area += Normal[iDim]*Normal[iDim];
9524  Area = sqrt (Area);
9525 
9526  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9527  UnitNormal[iDim] = Normal[iDim]/Area;
9528 
9529  /*--- Current solution at this boundary node ---*/
9530 
9531  V_domain = node[iPoint]->GetPrimitive();
9532 
9533  /*--- Subsonic nacelle inflow: there is one incoming characteristic,
9534  therefore one variable can be specified (back pressure) and is used
9535  to update the conservative variables.
9536 
9537  Compute the entropy and the acoustic variable. These
9538  riemann invariants, as well as the tangential velocity components,
9539  are extrapolated. ---*/
9540 
9541  Density = V_domain[nDim+2];
9542  Velocity2 = 0.0; Vn = 0.0;
9543  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
9544  Velocity[iDim] = V_domain[iDim+1];
9545  Velocity2 += Velocity[iDim]*Velocity[iDim];
9546  Vn += Velocity[iDim]*UnitNormal[iDim];
9547  }
9548  Pressure = V_domain[nDim+1];
9549  SoundSpeed = sqrt(Gamma*Pressure/Density);
9550  Entropy = Pressure*pow(1.0/Density, Gamma);
9551  Riemann = Vn + 2.0*SoundSpeed/Gamma_Minus_One;
9552 
9553  /*--- Compute the new fictious state at the outlet ---*/
9554 
9555  Density = pow(Inflow_Pressure/Entropy,1.0/Gamma);
9556  Pressure = Inflow_Pressure;
9557  SoundSpeed = sqrt(Gamma*Inflow_Pressure/Density);
9558  Vn_Exit = Riemann - 2.0*SoundSpeed/Gamma_Minus_One;
9559  Velocity2 = 0.0;
9560  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
9561  Velocity[iDim] = Velocity[iDim] + (Vn_Exit-Vn)*UnitNormal[iDim];
9562  Velocity2 += Velocity[iDim]*Velocity[iDim];
9563  }
9564 
9565  Energy = Inflow_Pressure/(Density*Gamma_Minus_One) + 0.5*Velocity2;
9566  if (tkeNeeded) Energy += GetTke_Inf();
9567 
9568  /*--- Conservative variables, using the derived quantities ---*/
9569 
9570  V_inflow[0] = Pressure / ( Gas_Constant * Density);
9571  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9572  V_inflow[iDim+1] = Velocity[iDim];
9573  V_inflow[nDim+1] = Pressure;
9574  V_inflow[nDim+2] = Density;
9575  V_inflow[nDim+3] = Energy + Pressure/Density;
9576 
9577  /*--- Set various quantities in the solver class ---*/
9578 
9579  conv_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
9580  conv_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_inflow);
9581 
9582  /*--- Compute the residual using an upwind scheme ---*/
9583 
9584  conv_numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
9585  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
9586 
9587  /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
9588 
9589  if (implicit)
9590  Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
9591 
9592  /*--- Viscous contribution ---*/
9593 
9594  if (viscous) {
9595 
9596  /*--- Set laminar and eddy viscosity at the infinity ---*/
9597 
9598  V_inflow[nDim+5] = node[iPoint]->GetLaminarViscosity();
9599  V_inflow[nDim+6] = node[iPoint]->GetEddyViscosity();
9600 
9601  /*--- Set the normal vector and the coordinates ---*/
9602 
9603  visc_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
9604  visc_numerics->SetCoord(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(), geometry->node[Point_Normal]->GetCoord());
9605 
9606  /*--- Primitive variables, and gradient ---*/
9607 
9608  visc_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_inflow);
9609  visc_numerics->SetPrimVarGradient(node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive(), node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive());
9610 
9611  /*--- Turbulent kinetic energy ---*/
9612 
9613  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST)
9614  visc_numerics->SetTurbKineticEnergy(solver_container[TURB_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0), solver_container[TURB_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0));
9615 
9616  /*--- Compute and update residual ---*/
9617 
9618  visc_numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
9619  LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(iPoint, Residual);
9620 
9621  /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
9622 
9623  if (implicit)
9624  Jacobian.SubtractBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
9625 
9626  }
9627 
9628  }
9629  }
9630 
9631  delete [] Normal;
9632 
9633 }

9635 void CEulerSolver::BC_Engine_Exhaust(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container, CNumerics *conv_numerics, CNumerics *visc_numerics, CConfig *config, unsigned short val_marker) {
9636 
9637  unsigned short iDim;
9638  unsigned long iVertex, iPoint, Point_Normal;
9639  su2double Exhaust_Pressure, Exhaust_Temperature, Velocity[3], Velocity2, H_Exhaust, Temperature, Riemann, Area, UnitNormal[3], Pressure, Density, Energy, Mach2, SoundSpeed2, SoundSpeed_Exhaust2, Vel_Mag, alpha, aa, bb, cc, dd, Flow_Dir[3];
9640  su2double *V_exhaust, *V_domain;
9641  su2double Gas_Constant = config->GetGas_ConstantND();
9642  bool implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme_Flow() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
9643  bool viscous = config->GetViscous();
9644  string Marker_Tag = config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(val_marker);
9645  bool tkeNeeded = (((config->GetKind_Solver() == RANS )|| (config->GetKind_Solver() == DISC_ADJ_RANS)) &&
9646  (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST));
9647  // su2double Target_Exhaust_Pressure, Exhaust_Pressure_old, Exhaust_Pressure_inc;
9648  // su2double DampingFactor = config->GetDamp_Engine_Exhaust();
9649  // su2double Baseline_Press = 0.75 * config->GetPressure_FreeStreamND();
9650 
9651  su2double *Normal = new su2double[nDim];
9652 
9653  /*--- Retrieve the specified exhaust pressure in the engine (non-dimensional). ---*/
9654 
9655  // Target_Exhaust_Pressure = config->GetExhaust_Pressure_Target(Marker_Tag) / config->GetPressure_Ref();
9656 
9657  /*--- Retrieve the old exhaust pressure in the engine exhaust (this has been computed in a preprocessing). ---*/
9658 
9659  // Exhaust_Pressure_old = config->GetExhaust_Pressure(Marker_Tag);
9660 
9661  /*--- Compute the Pressure increment ---*/
9662 
9663  // Exhaust_Pressure_inc = (1.0 - (Exhaust_Pressure_old/Target_Exhaust_Pressure)) * Baseline_Press;
9664 
9665  /*--- Estimate the new exhaust pressure ---*/
9666 
9667  // Exhaust_Pressure = (1.0 - DampingFactor) * Exhaust_Pressure_old + DampingFactor * (Exhaust_Pressure_old + Exhaust_Pressure_inc);
9668 
9669  /*--- The temperature is given (no iteration is required) ---*/
9670 
9671  Exhaust_Temperature = config->GetExhaust_Temperature_Target(Marker_Tag);
9672  Exhaust_Temperature /= config->GetTemperature_Ref();
9673 
9674  /*--- The pressure is given (no iteration is required) ---*/
9675  /*--- CHECK: the above iterative process is overwritten on the next line. ---*/
9676 
9677  Exhaust_Pressure = config->GetExhaust_Pressure_Target(Marker_Tag);
9678  Exhaust_Pressure /= config->GetPressure_Ref();
9679 
9680  /*--- Loop over all the vertices on this boundary marker ---*/
9681 
9682  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[val_marker]; iVertex++) {
9683 
9684  /*--- Allocate the value at the exhaust ---*/
9685 
9686  V_exhaust = GetCharacPrimVar(val_marker, iVertex);
9687 
9688  iPoint = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNode();
9689 
9690  /*--- Check if the node belongs to the domain (i.e, not a halo node) ---*/
9691 
9692  if (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain()) {
9693 
9694  /*--- Index of the closest interior node ---*/
9695 
9696  Point_Normal = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal_Neighbor();
9697 
9698  /*--- Normal vector for this vertex (negate for outward convention) ---*/
9699 
9700  geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Normal);
9701  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Normal[iDim] = -Normal[iDim];
9702 
9703  Area = 0.0;
9704  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9705  Area += Normal[iDim]*Normal[iDim];
9706  Area = sqrt (Area);
9707 
9708  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9709  UnitNormal[iDim] = Normal[iDim]/Area;
9710 
9711  /*--- Current solution at this boundary node ---*/
9712 
9713  V_domain = node[iPoint]->GetPrimitive();
9714 
9715  /*--- Subsonic inflow: there is one outgoing characteristic (u-c),
9716  therefore we can specify all but one state variable at the inlet.
9717  The outgoing Riemann invariant provides the final piece of info. ---*/
9718 
9719  /*--- Store primitives and set some variables for clarity. ---*/
9720 
9721  Density = V_domain[nDim+2];
9722  Velocity2 = 0.0;
9723  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
9724  Velocity[iDim] = V_domain[iDim+1];
9725  Velocity2 += Velocity[iDim]*Velocity[iDim];
9726  }
9727  Energy = V_domain[nDim+3] - V_domain[nDim+1]/V_domain[nDim+2];
9728  Pressure = V_domain[nDim+1];
9729  H_Exhaust = (Gamma*Gas_Constant/Gamma_Minus_One)*Exhaust_Temperature;
9730  SoundSpeed2 = Gamma*Pressure/Density;
9731 
9732  /*--- Compute the acoustic Riemann invariant that is extrapolated
9733  from the domain interior. ---*/
9734 
9735  Riemann = 2.0*sqrt(SoundSpeed2)/Gamma_Minus_One;
9736  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9737  Riemann += Velocity[iDim]*UnitNormal[iDim];
9738 
9739  /*--- Total speed of sound ---*/
9740 
9741  SoundSpeed_Exhaust2 = Gamma_Minus_One*(H_Exhaust - (Energy + Pressure/Density)+0.5*Velocity2) + SoundSpeed2;
9742 
9743  /*--- The flow direction is defined by the surface normal ---*/
9744 
9745  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9746  Flow_Dir[iDim] = -UnitNormal[iDim];
9747 
9748  /*--- Dot product of normal and flow direction. This should
9749  be negative due to outward facing boundary normal convention. ---*/
9750 
9751  alpha = 0.0;
9752  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9753  alpha += UnitNormal[iDim]*Flow_Dir[iDim];
9754 
9755  /*--- Coefficients in the quadratic equation for the velocity ---*/
9756 
9757  aa = 1.0 + 0.5*Gamma_Minus_One*alpha*alpha;
9758  bb = -1.0*Gamma_Minus_One*alpha*Riemann;
9759  cc = 0.5*Gamma_Minus_One*Riemann*Riemann - 2.0*SoundSpeed_Exhaust2/Gamma_Minus_One;
9760 
9761  /*--- Solve quadratic equation for velocity magnitude. Value must
9762  be positive, so the choice of root is clear. ---*/
9763 
9764  dd = bb*bb - 4.0*aa*cc;
9765  dd = sqrt(max(0.0, dd));
9766  Vel_Mag = (-bb + dd)/(2.0*aa);
9767 
9768  if (Vel_Mag >= 0.0) {
9769 
9770  Velocity2 = Vel_Mag*Vel_Mag;
9771 
9772  /*--- Compute speed of sound from total speed of sound eqn. ---*/
9773 
9774  SoundSpeed2 = SoundSpeed_Exhaust2 - 0.5*Gamma_Minus_One*Velocity2;
9775  Mach2 = Velocity2/SoundSpeed2;
9776  Velocity2 = Mach2*SoundSpeed2;
9777  Vel_Mag = sqrt(Velocity2);
9778  SoundSpeed2 = SoundSpeed_Exhaust2 - 0.5*Gamma_Minus_One*Velocity2;
9779 
9780  /*--- Compute new velocity vector at the inlet ---*/
9781 
9782  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9783  Velocity[iDim] = Vel_Mag*Flow_Dir[iDim];
9784 
9785  /*--- Static temperature from the speed of sound relation ---*/
9786 
9787  Temperature = SoundSpeed2/(Gamma*Gas_Constant);
9788 
9789  /*--- Static pressure using isentropic relation at a point ---*/
9790 
9791  Pressure = Exhaust_Pressure*pow((Temperature/Exhaust_Temperature), Gamma/Gamma_Minus_One);
9792 
9793  /*--- Density at the exhaust from the gas law ---*/
9794 
9795  Density = Pressure/(Gas_Constant*Temperature);
9796 
9797  /*--- Using pressure, density, & velocity, compute the energy ---*/
9798 
9799  Energy = Pressure/(Density*Gamma_Minus_One) + 0.5*Velocity2;
9800  if (tkeNeeded) Energy += GetTke_Inf();
9801 
9802  /*--- Primitive variables, using the derived quantities ---*/
9803 
9804  V_exhaust[0] = Temperature;
9805  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9806  V_exhaust[iDim+1] = Velocity[iDim];
9807  V_exhaust[nDim+1] = Pressure;
9808  V_exhaust[nDim+2] = Density;
9809  V_exhaust[nDim+3] = Energy + Pressure/Density;
9810 
9811  }
9812 
9813  /*--- The flow goes in the wrong direction ---*/
9814 
9815  else {
9816 
9817  V_exhaust[0] = V_domain[0];
9818  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9819  V_exhaust[iDim+1] = V_domain[iDim+1];
9820  V_exhaust[nDim+1] = V_domain[nDim+1];
9821  V_exhaust[nDim+2] = V_domain[nDim+2];
9822  V_exhaust[nDim+3] = V_domain[nDim+3];
9823 
9824  }
9825 
9826  /*--- Set various quantities in the solver class ---*/
9827 
9828  conv_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
9829  conv_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_exhaust);
9830 
9831  /*--- Compute the residual using an upwind scheme ---*/
9832 
9833  conv_numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
9834  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
9835 
9836  /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
9837 
9838  if (implicit)
9839  Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
9840 
9841  /*--- Viscous contribution ---*/
9842 
9843  if (viscous) {
9844 
9845  /*--- Set laminar and eddy viscosity at the infinity ---*/
9846 
9847  V_exhaust[nDim+5] = node[iPoint]->GetLaminarViscosity();
9848  V_exhaust[nDim+6] = node[iPoint]->GetEddyViscosity();
9849 
9850  /*--- Set the normal vector and the coordinates ---*/
9851 
9852  visc_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
9853  visc_numerics->SetCoord(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(), geometry->node[Point_Normal]->GetCoord());
9854 
9855  /*--- Primitive variables, and gradient ---*/
9856 
9857  visc_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_exhaust);
9858  visc_numerics->SetPrimVarGradient(node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive(), node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive());
9859 
9860  /*--- Turbulent kinetic energy ---*/
9861 
9862  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST)
9863  visc_numerics->SetTurbKineticEnergy(solver_container[TURB_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0), solver_container[TURB_SOL]->node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0));
9864 
9865  /*--- Compute and update residual ---*/
9866 
9867  visc_numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
9868  LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(iPoint, Residual);
9869 
9870  /*--- Jacobian contribution for implicit integration ---*/
9871 
9872  if (implicit)
9873  Jacobian.SubtractBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
9874 
9875  }
9876 
9877  }
9878  }
9879 
9880  delete [] Normal;
9881 
9882 }

9884 void CEulerSolver::BC_Engine_Bleed(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container, CNumerics *conv_numerics, CNumerics *visc_numerics, CConfig *config, unsigned short val_marker) {
9885 
9886  unsigned short iDim;
9887  unsigned long iVertex, iPoint, Point_Normal;
9888  su2double Bleed_Pressure, Target_Bleed_MassFlow, Bleed_Pressure_old, Bleed_MassFlow_old, Bleed_Pressure_inc, Bleed_Temperature, Velocity[3], Velocity2, H_Bleed, Temperature, Riemann, Area, UnitNormal[3], Pressure, Density, Energy, Mach2, SoundSpeed2, SoundSpeed_Bleed2, Vel_Mag, alpha, aa, bb, cc, dd, Flow_Dir[3];
9889  su2double *V_bleed, *V_domain;
9890  su2double Gas_Constant = config->GetGas_ConstantND();
9891 
9892  su2double DampingFactor = config->GetDamp_Engine_Bleed();
9893  bool implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme_Flow() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
9894  bool viscous = config->GetViscous();
9895  string Marker_Tag = config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(val_marker);
9896  bool tkeNeeded = (((config->GetKind_Solver() == RANS )|| (config->GetKind_Solver() == DISC_ADJ_RANS)) &&
9897  (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() == SST));
9898  su2double Baseline_Press = 0.25 * config->GetPressure_FreeStreamND();
9899 
9900  su2double *Normal = new su2double[nDim];
9901 
9902  /*--- Retrieve the specified target bleed mass flow in the engine (non-dimensional). ---*/
9903 
9904  Target_Bleed_MassFlow = config->GetBleed_MassFlow_Target(Marker_Tag) / (config->GetDensity_Ref() * config->GetVelocity_Ref());
9905 
9906  /*--- Retrieve the old Bleed pressure and mass flow rate number in the engine bleed (this has been computed in a preprocessing). ---*/
9907 
9908  Bleed_Pressure_old = config->GetBleed_Pressure(Marker_Tag);
9909  Bleed_MassFlow_old = config->GetBleed_MassFlow(Marker_Tag);
9910 
9911  /*--- Compute the Pressure increment (note that increasing pressure also increases mass flow rate) ---*/
9912 
9913  Bleed_Pressure_inc = (1.0 - (Bleed_MassFlow_old/Target_Bleed_MassFlow)) * Baseline_Press;
9914 
9915  /*--- Estimate the new bleed pressure ---*/
9916 
9917  Bleed_Pressure = (1.0 - DampingFactor)*Bleed_Pressure_old + DampingFactor * (Bleed_Pressure_old + Bleed_Pressure_inc);
9918 
9919  /*--- The temperature is given (no iteration is required) ---*/
9920 
9921  Bleed_Temperature = config->GetBleed_Temperature_Target(Marker_Tag);
9922  Bleed_Temperature /= config->GetTemperature_Ref();
9923 
9924  /*--- Loop over all the vertices on this boundary marker ---*/
9925 
9926  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[val_marker]; iVertex++) {
9927 
9928  /*--- Allocate the value at the exhaust ---*/
9929 
9930  V_bleed = GetCharacPrimVar(val_marker, iVertex);
9931 
9932  iPoint = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNode();
9933 
9934  /*--- Check if the node belongs to the domain (i.e, not a halo node) ---*/
9935 
9936  if (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain()) {
9937 
9938  /*--- Index of the closest interior node ---*/
9939 
9940  Point_Normal = geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal_Neighbor();
9941 
9942  /*--- Normal vector for this vertex (negate for outward convention) ---*/
9943 
9944  geometry->vertex[val_marker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Normal);
9945  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Normal[iDim] = -Normal[iDim];
9946 
9947  Area = 0.0;
9948  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9949  Area += Normal[iDim]*Normal[iDim];
9950  Area = sqrt (Area);
9951 
9952  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9953  UnitNormal[iDim] = Normal[iDim]/Area;
9954 
9955  /*--- Current solution at this boundary node ---*/
9956 
9957  V_domain = node[iPoint]->GetPrimitive();
9958 
9959  /*--- Subsonic inflow: there is one outgoing characteristic (u-c),
9960  therefore we can specify all but one state variable at the inlet.
9961  The outgoing Riemann invariant provides the final piece of info. ---*/
9962 
9963  /*--- Store primitives and set some variables for clarity. ---*/
9964 
9965  Density = V_domain[nDim+2];
9966  Velocity2 = 0.0;
9967  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
9968  Velocity[iDim] = V_domain[iDim+1];
9969  Velocity2 += Velocity[iDim]*Velocity[iDim];
9970  }
9971  Energy = V_domain[nDim+3] - V_domain[nDim+1]/V_domain[nDim+2];
9972  Pressure = V_domain[nDim+1];
9973  H_Bleed = (Gamma*Gas_Constant/Gamma_Minus_One)*Bleed_Temperature;
9974  SoundSpeed2 = Gamma*Pressure/Density;
9975 
9976  /*--- Compute the acoustic Riemann invariant that is extrapolated
9977  from the domain interior. ---*/
9978 
9979  Riemann = 2.0*sqrt(SoundSpeed2)/Gamma_Minus_One;
9980  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9981  Riemann += Velocity[iDim]*UnitNormal[iDim];
9982 
9983  /*--- Total speed of sound ---*/
9984 
9985  SoundSpeed_Bleed2 = Gamma_Minus_One*(H_Bleed - (Energy + Pressure/Density)+0.5*Velocity2) + SoundSpeed2;
9986 
9987  /*--- The flow direction is defined by the surface normal ---*/
9988 
9989  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9990  Flow_Dir[iDim] = -UnitNormal[iDim];
9991 
9992  /*--- Dot product of normal and flow direction. This should
9993  be negative due to outward facing boundary normal convention. ---*/
9994 
9995  alpha = 0.0;
9996  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
9997  alpha += UnitNormal[iDim]*Flow_Dir[iDim];
9998 
9999  /*--- Coefficients in the quadratic equation for the velocity ---*/
10000 
10001  aa = 1.0 + 0.5*Gamma_Minus_One*alpha*alpha;
10002  bb = -1.0*Gamma_Minus_One*alpha*Riemann;
10003  cc = 0.5*Gamma_Minus_One*Riemann*Riemann - 2.0*SoundSpeed_Bleed2/Gamma_Minus_One;
10004 
10005  /*--- Solve quadratic equation for velocity magnitude. Value must
10006  be positive, so the choice of root is clear. ---*/
10007 
10008  dd = bb*bb - 4.0*aa*cc;
10009  dd = sqrt(max(0.0, dd));
10010  Vel_Mag = (-bb + dd)/(2.0*aa);
10011 
10012  if (Vel_Mag >= 0.0) {
10013 
10014  Velocity2 = Vel_Mag*Vel_Mag;
10015 
10016  /*--- Compute speed of sound from total speed of sound eqn. ---*/
10017 
10018  SoundSpeed2 = SoundSpeed_Bleed2 - 0.5*Gamma_Minus_One*Velocity2;
10019 
10020  /*--- Mach squared (cut between 0-1), use to adapt velocity ---*/
10021 
10022  Mach2 = Velocity2/SoundSpeed2;
10023  Mach2 = min(1.0, Mach2);
10024  Velocity2 = Mach2*SoundSpeed2;
10025  Vel_Mag = sqrt(Velocity2);
10026  SoundSpeed2 = SoundSpeed_Bleed2 - 0.5*Gamma_Minus_One*Velocity2;
10027

10032

10034 
10035  Temperature = SoundSpeed2/(Gamma*Gas_Constant);
10036 
10037  /*--- Static pressure using isentropic relation at a point ---*/
10038 
10039  Pressure = Bleed_Pressure*pow((Temperature/Bleed_Temperature), Gamma/Gamma_Minus_One);
10040 
10041  /*--- Density at the inlet from the gas law ---*/
10042 
10043  Density = Pressure/(Gas_Constant*Temperature);
10044

10046

10054  V_bleed[iDim+1] = Velocity[iDim];
10055  V_bleed[nDim+1] = Pressure;
10056  V_bleed[nDim+2] = Density;
10057  V_bleed[nDim+3] = Energy + Pressure/Density;
10058 
10059  }
10060 
10061  /*--- The flow goes in the wrong direction ---*/
10062 
10063  else {
10064 
10065  V_bleed[0] = V_domain[0];
10066  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
10067  V_bleed[iDim+1] = V_domain[iDim+1];
10068  V_bleed[nDim+1] = V_domain[nDim+1];
10069  V_bleed[nDim+2] = V_domain[nDim+2];
10070  V_bleed[nDim+3] = V_domain[nDim+3];
10071 
10072  }

10083

10085

10087  Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
10088

10090 
10091  if (viscous) {
10092 
10093  /*--- Set laminar and eddy viscosity at the infinity ---*/
10094 
10095  V_bleed[nDim+5] = node[iPoint]->GetLaminarViscosity();
10096  V_bleed[nDim+6] = node[iPoint]->GetEddyViscosity();
10097 
10098  /*--- Set the normal vector and the coordinates ---*/
10099 
10100  visc_numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
10101  visc_numerics->SetCoord(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(), geometry->node[Point_Normal]->GetCoord());
10102

10104 
10105  visc_numerics->SetPrimitive(V_domain, V_bleed);
10106  visc_numerics->SetPrimVarGradient(node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive(), node[iPoint]->GetGradient_Primitive());

10112

10114

10163

10180

10184  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Normal[iDim] = -Normal[iDim];
10185  numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
10186

10195 
10196  }

10199  }
10200  }
