10548 
10549 void CEulerSolver::BC_ActDisk_Boundary(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container, CNumerics *numerics,
10550  CConfig *config) {
10551 
10552  unsigned long iVertex, iPoint, jPoint, Pin = 0, Pout = 0, jProcessor;
10553  unsigned short iDim, iVar, iMarker;
10554  int iProcessor;
10555  su2double *Coord, radius, DeltaP_avg, DeltaP_tip, DeltaT_avg, DeltaT_tip,
10556  Radial[3] = {0.0,0.0,0.0}, Tangent[3] = {0.0,0.0,0.0}, Normal[3] = {0.0,0.0,0.0},
10557  UnitRadial[3] = {0.0,0.0,0.0}, UnitTangent[3] = {0.0,0.0,0.0}, UnitNormal[3] = {0.0,0.0,0.0};
10558  su2double H_in_ghost, P_in_ghost, Vel_Swirl_out_ghost, T_in_ghost, Rho_in_ghost, sos_in_ghost, Area, Vel_in_ghost;
10559  su2double H_out_ghost, P_out_ghost, T_out_ghost, Rho_out_ghost, sos_out_ghost, Vel_Normal_in, Rho_in, Vel_Normal_out_ghost, Vel_out_ghost;
10560 
10561  bool implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme_Flow() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
10562  unsigned short nMarker_ActDisk_Inlet = config->GetnMarker_ActDisk_Inlet();
10563  // su2double DampingFactor = 0.75;
10564 
10565  if (nMarker_ActDisk_Inlet != 0) {
10566 
10567  su2double *PrimVar_out = new su2double[nPrimVar];
10568  su2double *PrimVar_in = new su2double[nPrimVar];
10569  su2double *MeanPrimVar = new su2double[nPrimVar];
10570  su2double *PrimVar_out_ghost = new su2double[nPrimVar];
10571  su2double *PrimVar_in_ghost = new su2double[nPrimVar];
10572  su2double *ActDisk_Jump = new su2double[nPrimVar];
10573  su2double *Buffer_Send_V = new su2double [nPrimVar];
10574  su2double *Buffer_Receive_V = new su2double [nPrimVar];
10575 
10576 #ifndef HAVE_MPI
10577  iProcessor = MASTER_NODE;
10578 #else
10579  MPI_Status status;
10580  //MPI_Status send_stat[1], recv_stat[1];
10581  //MPI_Request send_req[1], recv_req[1];
10582  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &iProcessor);
10583 #endif
10584 
10585  /*--- Identify the points that should be sended in a MPI implementation.
10586  Do the send process, by the moment we are sending each node individually, this must be changed---*/
10587 
10588 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
10589 
10590  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
10591 
10592  if ((config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == ACTDISK_INLET) ||
10593  (config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == ACTDISK_OUTLET)) {
10594 
10595  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
10596 
10597  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
10598 
10599  if (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain()) {
10600 
10601  /*--- Find the associate pair to the original node ---*/
10602 
10603  jPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetDonorPoint();
10604  jProcessor = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetDonorProcessor();
10605 
10606  /*--- We only send the information that belong to other boundary, using jPoint as the ID for the message ---*/
10607 
10608  if ((int)jProcessor != iProcessor) {
10609 
10610  /*--- Copy the primitive variables ---*/
10611 
10612  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nPrimVar; iVar++)
10613  Buffer_Send_V[iVar] = node[iPoint]->GetPrimitive(iVar);
10614 
10615  SU2_MPI::Bsend(Buffer_Send_V, nPrimVar, MPI_DOUBLE, jProcessor, iPoint, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
10616 
10617  // SU2_MPI::Isend(Buffer_Send_V, nPrimVar, MPI_DOUBLE, jProcessor, iPoint, MPI_COMM_WORLD, &send_req[0]);
10618  // SU2_MPI::Waitall(1, send_req, send_stat);
10619 
10620  }
10621 
10622  }
10623  }
10624  }
10625  }
10626 
10627 #endif
10628 
10629  /*--- Evaluate the fluxes, the donor solution has been sended using MPI ---*/
10630 
10631  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
10632 
10633  if ((config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == ACTDISK_INLET) ||
10634  (config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == ACTDISK_OUTLET)) {
10635 
10636  unsigned short boundary = config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker);
10637  su2double *Origin = config->GetActDisk_Origin(config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker));
10638  su2double R_root = config->GetActDisk_RootRadius(config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker));
10639  su2double R_tip = config->GetActDisk_TipRadius(config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker));
10640  su2double Target_Press_Jump = config->GetActDisk_PressJump(config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker))/ config->GetPressure_Ref();
10641  su2double Target_Temp_Jump = config->GetActDisk_TempJump(config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker))/ config->GetTemperature_Ref();
10642  su2double Omega = config->GetActDisk_Omega(config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker))*(PI_NUMBER/30.0);
10643  unsigned short Distribution = config->GetActDisk_Distribution(config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker));
10644 
10645  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
10646 
10647  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
10648 
10649  if (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain()) {
10650 
10651  /*--- Find the associate pair to the original node ---*/
10652 
10653  jPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetDonorPoint();
10654  jProcessor = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetDonorProcessor();
10655 
10656  /*--- Receive the information, using jPoint as the ID for the message ---*/
10657 
10658  if ((int)jProcessor != iProcessor) {
10659 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
10660 
10661  SU2_MPI::Recv(Buffer_Receive_V, nPrimVar, MPI_DOUBLE, jProcessor, jPoint, MPI_COMM_WORLD, &status);
10662 
10663  // SU2_MPI::Irecv(Buffer_Receive_V, nPrimVar, MPI_DOUBLE, jProcessor, jPoint, MPI_COMM_WORLD, &recv_req[0]);
10664  // SU2_MPI::Waitall(1, send_req, send_stat);
10665 
10666 #endif
10667  }
10668  else {
10669 
10670  /*--- The point is in the same processor... no MPI required ---*/
10671 
10672  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nPrimVar; iVar++)
10673  Buffer_Receive_V[iVar] = node[jPoint]->GetPrimitive(iVar);
10674 
10675  }
10676 
10677  /*--- Identify the inner and the outer point (based on the normal direction) ---*/
10678 
10679  if (boundary == ACTDISK_INLET) {
10680 
10681  Pin = iPoint;
10682 
10683  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nPrimVar; iVar++) {
10684  PrimVar_out[iVar] = Buffer_Receive_V[iVar];
10685  PrimVar_in[iVar] = node[Pin]->GetPrimitive(iVar);
10686  }
10687 
10688  }
10689  if (boundary == ACTDISK_OUTLET) {
10690 
10691  Pout = iPoint;
10692 
10693  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nPrimVar; iVar++) {
10694  PrimVar_out[iVar] = node[Pout]->GetPrimitive(iVar);
10695  PrimVar_in[iVar] = Buffer_Receive_V[iVar];
10696  }
10697 
10698  }
10699 
10700  /*--- Set the jump in the actuator disk ---*/
10701 
10702  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nPrimVar; iVar++) {
10703  ActDisk_Jump[iVar] = 0.0;
10704  }
10705 
10706  /*--- Compute the distance to the center of the rotor ---*/
10707 
10708  Coord = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord();
10709  radius = 0.0;
10710  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
10711  radius += (Coord[iDim]-Origin[iDim])*(Coord[iDim]-Origin[iDim]);
10712  radius = sqrt(radius);
10713 
10714  /*--- Compute the pressure jump ---*/
10715 
10716  // su2double Press_Jump = fabs(PrimVar_in[nDim+1]-PrimVar_in[nDim+1]);
10717  // su2double Press_inc = (1.0 - (Press_Jump/Target_Press_Jump)) * 0.01 * config->GetPressure_FreeStreamND();
10718  // DeltaP_avg = (1.0 - DampingFactor)*Press_Jump + DampingFactor * (Press_Jump + Press_inc);
10719 
10720  DeltaP_avg = Target_Press_Jump;
10721  if (Distribution == 1) {
10722  DeltaP_tip = (3.0/2.0)*DeltaP_avg*R_tip*(R_tip*R_tip-R_root*R_root)/(R_tip*R_tip*R_tip-R_root*R_root*R_root);
10723  ActDisk_Jump[nDim+1] = DeltaP_tip*radius/R_tip;
10724  }
10725  else
10726  ActDisk_Jump[nDim+1] = DeltaP_avg;
10727 
10728  /*--- Compute the temperature jump ---*/
10729 
10730  // su2double Temp_Jump = fabs(PrimVar_in[0]-PrimVar_in[0]);
10731  // su2double Temp_inc = (1.0 - (Temp_Jump/Target_Temp_Jump)) * 0.01 * config->GetTemperature_FreeStreamND();
10732  // DeltaT_avg = (1.0 - DampingFactor)*Temp_Jump + DampingFactor * (Temp_Jump + Temp_inc);
10733 
10734  DeltaT_avg = Target_Temp_Jump;
10735  if (Distribution == 1) {
10736  DeltaT_tip = (3.0/2.0)*DeltaT_avg*R_tip*(R_tip*R_tip-R_root*R_root)/(R_tip*R_tip*R_tip-R_root*R_root*R_root);
10737  ActDisk_Jump[0] = DeltaT_tip*radius/R_tip;
10738  }
10739  else
10740  ActDisk_Jump[0] = DeltaT_avg;
10741 
10742  /*--- Inner point ---*/
10743 
10744  if (boundary == ACTDISK_INLET) {
10745 
10746  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nPrimVar; iVar++)
10747  PrimVar_in_ghost[iVar] = PrimVar_out[iVar] - ActDisk_Jump[iVar];
10748 
10749  /*--- Check that this is a meaningful state ---*/
10750 
10751  P_in_ghost = PrimVar_in_ghost[nDim+1];
10752  T_in_ghost = PrimVar_in_ghost[0];
10753 
10754  FluidModel->SetTDState_PT(P_in_ghost, T_in_ghost);
10755  Rho_in_ghost = FluidModel->GetDensity();
10756  sos_in_ghost = FluidModel->GetSoundSpeed();
10757 
10758  /*--- Find unit normal to the actuator disk ---*/
10759 
10760  geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Normal);
10761 
10762  Area = 0.0; for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Area += Normal[iDim]*Normal[iDim]; Area = sqrt(Area);
10763  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) { UnitNormal[iDim] = -Normal[iDim]/Area; }
10764 
10765  /*--- Impose only normal velocity on the disk inflow ---*/
10766 
10767  Vel_in_ghost = 0.0;
10768  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
10769  Vel_in_ghost += PrimVar_in[iDim+1]*UnitNormal[iDim];
10770  }
10771 
10772  /*--- COmpute the enthalpy ---*/
10773 
10774  H_in_ghost = FluidModel->GetStaticEnergy() + 0.5*Vel_in_ghost*Vel_in_ghost + P_in_ghost/Rho_in_ghost;
10775 
10776  PrimVar_in_ghost[0] = T_in_ghost;
10777  PrimVar_in_ghost[1] = Vel_in_ghost*UnitNormal[0];
10778  PrimVar_in_ghost[2] = Vel_in_ghost*UnitNormal[1];
10779  PrimVar_in_ghost[3] = Vel_in_ghost*UnitNormal[2];
10780  PrimVar_in_ghost[nDim+1]= P_in_ghost;
10781  PrimVar_in_ghost[nDim+2]= Rho_in_ghost;
10782  PrimVar_in_ghost[nDim+3]= H_in_ghost;
10783  PrimVar_in_ghost[nDim+4]= sos_in_ghost;
10784 
10785  numerics->SetPrimitive(PrimVar_in, PrimVar_in_ghost);
10786 
10787  }
10788 
10789  /*--- Outer point ---*/
10790 
10791  if (boundary == ACTDISK_OUTLET) {
10792 
10793  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nPrimVar; iVar++)
10794  PrimVar_out_ghost[iVar] = PrimVar_in[iVar] + ActDisk_Jump[iVar];
10795 
10796  /*--- Check that this is a meaningful state ---*/
10797 
10798  P_out_ghost = PrimVar_out_ghost[nDim+1];
10799  T_out_ghost = PrimVar_out_ghost[0];
10800 
10801  FluidModel->SetTDState_PT(P_out_ghost, T_out_ghost);
10802  Rho_out_ghost = FluidModel->GetDensity();
10803  sos_out_ghost = FluidModel->GetSoundSpeed();
10804 
10805  /*--- Find unit normal to the actuator disk ---*/
10806 
10807  geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Normal);
10808 
10809  Area = 0.0; for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Area += Normal[iDim]*Normal[iDim]; Area = sqrt(Area);
10810  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) { UnitNormal[iDim] = Normal[iDim]/Area; }
10811 
10812  /*--- Find unit radial to the actuator disk ---*/
10813 
10814  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
10815  Radial[iDim] = Coord[iDim]-Origin[iDim];
10816 
10817  Area = 0.0; for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Area += Radial[iDim]*Radial[iDim]; Area = sqrt(Area);
10818  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) { UnitRadial[iDim] = Radial[iDim]/Area; }
10819 
10820  /*--- Find unit tangent to the actuator disk ---*/
10821 
10822  Tangent[0] = UnitNormal[1]*UnitRadial[2] - UnitNormal[2]*UnitRadial[1];
10823  Tangent[1] = UnitNormal[2]*UnitRadial[0] - UnitNormal[0]*UnitRadial[2];
10824  Tangent[2] = UnitNormal[0]*UnitRadial[1] - UnitNormal[1]*UnitRadial[0];
10825 
10826  Area = 0.0; for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Area += Tangent[iDim]*Tangent[iDim]; Area = sqrt(Area);
10827  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) { UnitTangent[iDim] = Tangent[iDim]/Area; }
10828 
10829  /*--- Normal velocity to the disk and density at the inlet---*/
10830 
10831  Vel_Normal_in = 0.0;
10832  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
10833  Vel_Normal_in += PrimVar_in[iDim+1]*UnitNormal[iDim];
10834  }
10835 
10836  Rho_in = PrimVar_in[nDim+2];
10837 
10838  /*--- Conservation of mass to evaluate velocity at the outlet ---*/
10839 
10840  Vel_out_ghost = (Rho_in*Vel_Normal_in)/Rho_out_ghost;
10841 
10842  /*--- Compute the swirl velocity (check the formula) ---*/
10843 
10844  if (Omega != 0.0)
10845  Vel_Swirl_out_ghost = Omega*radius*(1.0-(1.0-sqrt(2.0*ActDisk_Jump[nDim+1]/(Rho_in*pow(Omega*radius, 2.0)))));
10846  else
10847  Vel_Swirl_out_ghost = 0.0;
10848 
10849  /*--- Compute normal component of the velocity ---*/
10850 
10851  Vel_Normal_out_ghost = sqrt(Vel_out_ghost*Vel_out_ghost-Vel_Swirl_out_ghost*Vel_Swirl_out_ghost);
10852 
10853  /*--- Compute total entalphy ---*/
10854 
10855  H_out_ghost = FluidModel->GetStaticEnergy() + 0.5*(Vel_Normal_out_ghost+Vel_Swirl_out_ghost)*(Vel_Normal_out_ghost+Vel_Swirl_out_ghost) + P_out_ghost/Rho_out_ghost;
10856 
10857  PrimVar_out_ghost[0] = T_out_ghost;
10858  PrimVar_out_ghost[1] = Vel_Normal_out_ghost*UnitNormal[0] + Vel_Swirl_out_ghost*UnitTangent[0];
10859  PrimVar_out_ghost[2] = Vel_Normal_out_ghost*UnitNormal[1] + Vel_Swirl_out_ghost*UnitTangent[1];
10860  PrimVar_out_ghost[3] = Vel_Normal_out_ghost*UnitNormal[2] + Vel_Swirl_out_ghost*UnitTangent[2];
10861  PrimVar_out_ghost[nDim+1]= P_out_ghost;
10862  PrimVar_out_ghost[nDim+2]= Rho_out_ghost;
10863  PrimVar_out_ghost[nDim+3]= H_out_ghost;
10864  PrimVar_out_ghost[nDim+4]= sos_out_ghost;
10865 
10866  numerics->SetPrimitive(PrimVar_out, PrimVar_out_ghost);
10867 
10868  }
10869 
10870  /*--- Set the normal vector ---*/
10871 
10872  geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Normal);
10873  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Normal[iDim] = -Normal[iDim];
10874  numerics->SetNormal(Normal);
10875 
10876  /*--- Compute the convective residual using an upwind scheme ---*/
10877 
10878  numerics->ComputeResidual(Residual, Jacobian_i, Jacobian_j, config);
10879 
10880  /*--- Add Residuals and Jacobians ---*/
10881 
10882  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
10883  if (implicit) Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
10884 
10885  }
10886 
10887  }
10888 
10889  }
10890 
10891  }
10892 
10893  /*--- We are using non-blocking communications ---*/
10894 
10895 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
10896 
10897  MPI_Barrier(MPI_COMM_WORLD);
10898 
10899 #endif
10900 
10901  /*--- Free locally allocated memory ---*/
10902 
10903  delete [] PrimVar_out;
10904  delete [] PrimVar_in;
10905  delete [] MeanPrimVar;
10906  delete [] PrimVar_out_ghost;
10907  delete [] PrimVar_in_ghost;
10908  delete [] ActDisk_Jump;
10909  delete[] Buffer_Send_V;
10910  delete[] Buffer_Receive_V;
10911 
10912  }
10913 
10914 }
10915 
10916 void CEulerSolver::BC_Dirichlet(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container,
10917  CConfig *config, unsigned short val_marker) { }
10918 
10919 void CEulerSolver::BC_Custom(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container, CNumerics *numerics, CConfig *config, unsigned short val_marker) { }
10920 
10921 void CEulerSolver::SetResidual_DualTime(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container, CConfig *config,
10922  unsigned short iRKStep, unsigned short iMesh, unsigned short RunTime_EqSystem) {
10923 
10924  /*--- Local variables ---*/
10925 
10926  unsigned short iVar, jVar, iMarker, iDim;
10927  unsigned long iPoint, jPoint, iEdge, iVertex;
10928 
10929  su2double *U_time_nM1, *U_time_n, *U_time_nP1;
10930  su2double Volume_nM1, Volume_nP1, TimeStep;
10931  su2double *Normal = NULL, *GridVel_i = NULL, *GridVel_j = NULL, Residual_GCL;
10932 
10933  bool implicit = (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme_Flow() == EULER_IMPLICIT);
10934  bool FlowEq = (RunTime_EqSystem == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS);
10935  bool AdjEq = (RunTime_EqSystem == RUNTIME_ADJFLOW_SYS);
10936  bool incompressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == INCOMPRESSIBLE);
10937  bool freesurface = (config->GetKind_Regime() == FREESURFACE);
10938  bool grid_movement = config->GetGrid_Movement();
10939 
10940  /*--- Store the physical time step ---*/
10941 
10942  TimeStep = config->GetDelta_UnstTimeND();
10943 
10944  /*--- Compute the dual time-stepping source term for static meshes ---*/
10945 
10946  if (!grid_movement) {
10947 
10948  /*--- Loop over all nodes (excluding halos) ---*/
10949 
10950  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPointDomain; iPoint++) {
10951 
10952  /*--- Retrieve the solution at time levels n-1, n, and n+1. Note that
10953  we are currently iterating on U^n+1 and that U^n & U^n-1 are fixed,
10954  previous solutions that are stored in memory. ---*/
10955 
10956  U_time_nM1 = node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n1();
10957  U_time_n = node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n();
10958  U_time_nP1 = node[iPoint]->GetSolution();
10959 
10960  /*--- CV volume at time n+1. As we are on a static mesh, the volume
10961  of the CV will remained fixed for all time steps. ---*/
10962 
10963  Volume_nP1 = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetVolume();
10964 
10965  /*--- Compute the dual time-stepping source term based on the chosen
10966  time discretization scheme (1st- or 2nd-order).---*/
10967 
10968  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
10969  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_1ST)
10970  Residual[iVar] = (U_time_nP1[iVar] - U_time_n[iVar])*Volume_nP1 / TimeStep;
10971  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_2ND)
10972  Residual[iVar] = ( 3.0*U_time_nP1[iVar] - 4.0*U_time_n[iVar]
10973  +1.0*U_time_nM1[iVar])*Volume_nP1 / (2.0*TimeStep);
10974  }
10975  if ((incompressible || freesurface) && (FlowEq || AdjEq)) Residual[0] = 0.0;
10976 
10977  /*--- Store the residual and compute the Jacobian contribution due
10978  to the dual time source term. ---*/
10979 
10980  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
10981  if (implicit) {
10982  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
10983  for (jVar = 0; jVar < nVar; jVar++) Jacobian_i[iVar][jVar] = 0.0;
10984  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_1ST)
10985  Jacobian_i[iVar][iVar] = Volume_nP1 / TimeStep;
10986  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_2ND)
10987  Jacobian_i[iVar][iVar] = (Volume_nP1*3.0)/(2.0*TimeStep);
10988  }
10989  if ((incompressible || freesurface) && (FlowEq || AdjEq)) Jacobian_i[0][0] = 0.0;
10990  Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
10991  }
10992  }
10993 
10994  }
10995 
10996  else {
10997 
10998  /*--- For unsteady flows on dynamic meshes (rigidly transforming or
10999  dynamically deforming), the Geometric Conservation Law (GCL) should be
11000  satisfied in conjunction with the ALE formulation of the governing
11001  equations. The GCL prevents accuracy issues caused by grid motion, i.e.
11002  a uniform free-stream should be preserved through a moving grid. First,
11003  we will loop over the edges and boundaries to compute the GCL component
11004  of the dual time source term that depends on grid velocities. ---*/
11005 
11006  for (iEdge = 0; iEdge < geometry->GetnEdge(); iEdge++) {
11007 
11008  /*--- Get indices for nodes i & j plus the face normal ---*/
11009 
11010  iPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(0);
11011  jPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(1);
11012  Normal = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNormal();
11013 
11014  /*--- Grid velocities stored at nodes i & j ---*/
11015 
11016  GridVel_i = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel();
11017  GridVel_j = geometry->node[jPoint]->GetGridVel();
11018 
11019  /*--- Compute the GCL term by averaging the grid velocities at the
11020  edge mid-point and dotting with the face normal. ---*/
11021 
11022  Residual_GCL = 0.0;
11023  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
11024  Residual_GCL += 0.5*(GridVel_i[iDim]+GridVel_j[iDim])*Normal[iDim];
11025 
11026  /*--- Compute the GCL component of the source term for node i ---*/
11027 
11028  U_time_n = node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n();
11029  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
11030  Residual[iVar] = U_time_n[iVar]*Residual_GCL;
11031  if ((incompressible || freesurface) && (FlowEq || AdjEq)) Residual[0] = 0.0;
11032  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
11033 
11034  /*--- Compute the GCL component of the source term for node j ---*/
11035 
11036  U_time_n = node[jPoint]->GetSolution_time_n();
11037  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
11038  Residual[iVar] = U_time_n[iVar]*Residual_GCL;
11039  if ((incompressible || freesurface) && (FlowEq || AdjEq)) Residual[0] = 0.0;
11040  LinSysRes.SubtractBlock(jPoint, Residual);
11041 
11042  }
11043 
11044  /*--- Loop over the boundary edges ---*/
11045 
11046  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < geometry->GetnMarker(); iMarker++) {
11047  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->GetnVertex(iMarker); iVertex++) {
11048 
11049  /*--- Get the index for node i plus the boundary face normal ---*/
11050 
11051  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
11052  Normal = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNormal();
11053 
11054  /*--- Grid velocities stored at boundary node i ---*/
11055 
11056  GridVel_i = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGridVel();
11057 
11058  /*--- Compute the GCL term by dotting the grid velocity with the face
11059  normal. The normal is negated to match the boundary convention. ---*/
11060 
11061  Residual_GCL = 0.0;
11062  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
11063  Residual_GCL -= 0.5*(GridVel_i[iDim]+GridVel_i[iDim])*Normal[iDim];
11064 
11065  /*--- Compute the GCL component of the source term for node i ---*/
11066 
11067  U_time_n = node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n();
11068  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++)
11069  Residual[iVar] = U_time_n[iVar]*Residual_GCL;
11070  if ((incompressible || freesurface) && (FlowEq || AdjEq)) Residual[0] = 0.0;
11071  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
11072 
11073  }
11074  }
11075 
11076  /*--- Loop over all nodes (excluding halos) to compute the remainder
11077  of the dual time-stepping source term. ---*/
11078 
11079  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPointDomain; iPoint++) {
11080 
11081  /*--- Retrieve the solution at time levels n-1, n, and n+1. Note that
11082  we are currently iterating on U^n+1 and that U^n & U^n-1 are fixed,
11083  previous solutions that are stored in memory. ---*/
11084 
11085  U_time_nM1 = node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n1();
11086  U_time_n = node[iPoint]->GetSolution_time_n();
11087  U_time_nP1 = node[iPoint]->GetSolution();
11088 
11089  /*--- CV volume at time n-1 and n+1. In the case of dynamically deforming
11090  grids, the volumes will change. On rigidly transforming grids, the
11091  volumes will remain constant. ---*/
11092 
11093  Volume_nM1 = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetVolume_nM1();
11094  Volume_nP1 = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetVolume();
11095 
11096  /*--- Compute the dual time-stepping source residual. Due to the
11097  introduction of the GCL term above, the remainder of the source residual
11098  due to the time discretization has a new form.---*/
11099 
11100  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
11101  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_1ST)
11102  Residual[iVar] = (U_time_nP1[iVar] - U_time_n[iVar])*(Volume_nP1/TimeStep);
11103  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_2ND)
11104  Residual[iVar] = (U_time_nP1[iVar] - U_time_n[iVar])*(3.0*Volume_nP1/(2.0*TimeStep))
11105  + (U_time_nM1[iVar] - U_time_n[iVar])*(Volume_nM1/(2.0*TimeStep));
11106  }
11107  if ((incompressible || freesurface) && (FlowEq || AdjEq)) Residual[0] = 0.0;
11108 
11109  /*--- Store the residual and compute the Jacobian contribution due
11110  to the dual time source term. ---*/
11111 
11112  LinSysRes.AddBlock(iPoint, Residual);
11113  if (implicit) {
11114  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
11115  for (jVar = 0; jVar < nVar; jVar++) Jacobian_i[iVar][jVar] = 0.0;
11116  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_1ST)
11117  Jacobian_i[iVar][iVar] = Volume_nP1/TimeStep;
11118  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_2ND)
11119  Jacobian_i[iVar][iVar] = (3.0*Volume_nP1)/(2.0*TimeStep);
11120  }
11121  if ((incompressible || freesurface) && (FlowEq || AdjEq)) Jacobian_i[0][0] = 0.0;
11122  Jacobian.AddBlock(iPoint, iPoint, Jacobian_i);
11123  }
11124  }
11125  }
11126 
11127 }
11128 
11129 void CEulerSolver::SetFlow_Displacement(CGeometry **flow_geometry, CVolumetricMovement *flow_grid_movement,
11130  CConfig *flow_config, CConfig *fea_config, CGeometry **fea_geometry, CSolver ***fea_solution) {
11131  unsigned short iDim;
11132  unsigned long iVertex;
11133  su2double *Coord, VarCoord[3] = {0,0,0};
11134 
11135  #ifndef HAVE_MPI
11136  unsigned long iPoint_Donor, iPoint;
11137  unsigned short iMarker;
11138  su2double *CoordDonor, *DisplacementDonor;
11139 
11140  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < flow_config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
11141 
11142  if (flow_config->GetMarker_All_FSIinterface(iMarker) != 0) {
11143 
11144  for(iVertex = 0; iVertex < flow_geometry[MESH_0]->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
11145 
11146  iPoint = flow_geometry[MESH_0]->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
11147 
11148  iPoint_Donor = flow_geometry[MESH_0]->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetDonorPoint();
11149 
11150  Coord = flow_geometry[MESH_0]->node[iPoint]->GetCoord();
11151 
11152  CoordDonor = fea_geometry[MESH_0]->node[iPoint_Donor]->GetCoord();
11153 
11154  /*--- The displacements come from the predicted solution ---*/
11155  DisplacementDonor = fea_solution[MESH_0][FEA_SOL]->node[iPoint_Donor]->GetSolution_Pred();
11156 
11157  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
11158 
11159  VarCoord[iDim] = (CoordDonor[iDim]+DisplacementDonor[iDim])-Coord[iDim];
11160 
11161  flow_geometry[MESH_0]->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->SetVarCoord(VarCoord);
11162  }
11163  }
11164  }
11165 
11166  #else
11167 
11168  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
11169  int size = SINGLE_NODE;
11170 
11171  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
11172  MPI_Comm_size(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &size);
11173 
11174  unsigned long nLocalVertexStruct = 0, nLocalVertexFlow = 0;
11175 
11176  unsigned short nMarkerFSI, nMarkerStruct, nMarkerFlow; // Number of markers on FSI problem, FEA and Flow side
11177  unsigned short iMarkerFSI, iMarkerStruct, iMarkerFlow; // Variables for iteration over markers
11178 
11179  unsigned long MaxLocalVertexStruct = 0, MaxLocalVertexFlow = 0;
11180 
11181  unsigned long nBuffer_StructCoord = 0, nBuffer_FlowNewCoord = 0;
11182  unsigned long nBuffer_DonorIndices = 0, nBuffer_SetIndex = 0;
11183 
11184  unsigned long Point_Flow, Point_Struct;
11185  long Point_Flow_Rcv, Processor_Flow_Rcv;
11186  unsigned long Processor_Flow;
11187 
11188  int Marker_Flow = -1, Marker_Struct = -1;
11189 
11190  int iProcessor, nProcessor = 0;
11191 
11192 
11193  su2double *Coord_Struct, *Displacement_Struct;
11194 
11195  /*--- Number of markers on the FSI interface ---*/
11196 
11197  nMarkerFSI = (flow_config->GetMarker_n_FSIinterface())/2;
11198  nMarkerStruct = fea_geometry[MESH_0]->GetnMarker();
11199  nMarkerFlow = flow_geometry[MESH_0]->GetnMarker();
11200 
11201  nProcessor = size;
11202 
11203  /*--- Outer loop over the markers on the FSI interface: compute one by one ---*/
11204  /*--- The tags are always an integer greater than 1: loop from 1 to nMarkerFSI ---*/
11205 
11206  for (iMarkerFSI = 1; iMarkerFSI <= nMarkerFSI; iMarkerFSI++){
11207 
11208  Marker_Struct = -1;
11209  Marker_Flow = -1;
11210 
11211  /*--- Initialize pointer buffers inside the loop, so we can delete for each marker. ---*/
11212  unsigned long Buffer_Send_nVertexStruct[1], *Buffer_Recv_nVertexStruct = NULL;
11213  unsigned long Buffer_Send_nVertexFlow[1], *Buffer_Recv_nVertexFlow = NULL;
11214 
11215  /*--- The markers on the fluid and structural side are tagged with the same index.
11216  *--- This is independent of the MPI domain decomposition.
11217  *--- We need to loop over all markers on structural side and get the number of nodes
11218  *--- that belong to each FSI marker for each processor ---*/
11219 
11220  /*--- On the structural side ---*/
11221 
11222  for (iMarkerStruct = 0; iMarkerStruct < nMarkerStruct; iMarkerStruct++){
11223  /*--- If the tag GetMarker_All_FSIinterface(iMarkerFEA) equals the index we are looping at ---*/
11224  if ( fea_config->GetMarker_All_FSIinterface(iMarkerStruct) == iMarkerFSI ){
11225  /*--- We have identified the local index of the FEA marker ---*/
11226  /*--- Store the number of local points that belong to markFEA on each processor ---*/
11227  /*--- This includes the halo nodes ---*/
11228  nLocalVertexStruct = fea_geometry[MESH_0]->GetnVertex(iMarkerStruct);
11229  /*--- Store the identifier for the structural marker ---*/
11230  Marker_Struct = iMarkerStruct;
11231  /*--- Exit the for loop: we have found the local index for iMarkerFSI on the FEA side ---*/
11232  break;
11233  }
11234  else {
11235  /*--- If the tag hasn't matched any tag within the FEA markers ---*/
11236  nLocalVertexStruct = 0;
11237  Marker_Struct = -1;
11238  }
11239  }
11240 
11241  /*--- On the fluid side ---*/
11242 
11243  for (iMarkerFlow = 0; iMarkerFlow < nMarkerFlow; iMarkerFlow++){
11244  /*--- If the tag GetMarker_All_FSIinterface(iMarkerFlow) equals the index we are looping at ---*/
11245  if ( flow_config->GetMarker_All_FSIinterface(iMarkerFlow) == iMarkerFSI ){
11246  /*--- We have identified the local index of the Flow marker ---*/
11247  /*--- Store the number of local points that belong to markFlow on each processor ---*/
11248  /*--- This includes the halo nodes ---*/
11249  nLocalVertexFlow = flow_geometry[MESH_0]->GetnVertex(iMarkerFlow);
11250  /*--- Store the identifier for the fluid marker ---*/
11251  Marker_Flow = iMarkerFlow;
11252  /*--- Exit the for loop: we have found the local index for iMarkerFSI on the FEA side ---*/
11253  break;
11254  }
11255  else {
11256  /*--- If the tag hasn't matched any tag within the Flow markers ---*/
11257  nLocalVertexFlow = 0;
11258  Marker_Flow = -1;
11259  }
11260  }
11261 
11262  Buffer_Send_nVertexStruct[0] = nLocalVertexStruct; // Retrieve total number of vertices on FEA marker
11263  Buffer_Send_nVertexFlow[0] = nLocalVertexFlow; // Retrieve total number of vertices on Flow marker
11264  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) Buffer_Recv_nVertexStruct = new unsigned long[size]; // Allocate memory to receive how many vertices are on each rank on the structural side
11265  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) Buffer_Recv_nVertexFlow = new unsigned long[size]; // Allocate memory to receive how many vertices are on each rank on the fluid side
11266 
11267  /*--- We receive MaxLocalVertexFEA as the maximum number of vertices in one single processor on the structural side---*/
11268  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&nLocalVertexStruct, &MaxLocalVertexStruct, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MPI_MAX, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
11269  /*--- We receive MaxLocalVertexFlow as the maximum number of vertices in one single processor on the fluid side ---*/
11270  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&nLocalVertexFlow, &MaxLocalVertexFlow, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MPI_MAX, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
11271 
11272  /*--- We gather a vector in MASTER_NODE that determines how many elements are there on each processor on the structural side ---*/
11273  SU2_MPI::Gather(&Buffer_Send_nVertexStruct, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, Buffer_Recv_nVertexStruct, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
11274  /*--- We gather a vector in MASTER_NODE that determines how many elements are there on each processor on the fluid side ---*/
11275  SU2_MPI::Gather(&Buffer_Send_nVertexFlow, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, Buffer_Recv_nVertexFlow, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
11276 
11277  /*--- We will be gathering the structural coordinates into the master node ---*/
11278  /*--- Then we will distribute them using a scatter operation into the appropriate fluid processor ---*/
11279  nBuffer_StructCoord = MaxLocalVertexStruct * nDim;
11280  nBuffer_FlowNewCoord = MaxLocalVertexFlow * nDim;
11281 
11282  /*--- We will be gathering donor index and donor processor (for structure -> donor = flow) ---*/
11283  /*--- Then we will pass on to the fluid side the index (flow point) to the appropriate processor ---*/
11284  nBuffer_DonorIndices = 2 * MaxLocalVertexStruct;
11285  nBuffer_SetIndex = MaxLocalVertexFlow;
11286 
11287  /*--- Send and Recv buffers ---*/
11288 
11289  /*--- Buffers to send and receive the structural coordinates ---*/
11290  su2double *Buffer_Send_StructCoord = new su2double[nBuffer_StructCoord];
11291  su2double *Buffer_Recv_StructCoord = NULL;
11292 
11293  /*--- Buffers to send and receive the donor index and processor ---*/
11294  long *Buffer_Send_DonorIndices = new long[nBuffer_DonorIndices];
11295  long *Buffer_Recv_DonorIndices = NULL;
11296 
11297  /*--- Buffers to send and receive the new fluid coordinates ---*/
11298  su2double *Buffer_Send_FlowNewCoord = NULL;
11299  su2double *Buffer_Recv_FlowNewCoord = new su2double[nBuffer_FlowNewCoord];
11300 
11301  /*--- Buffers to send and receive the fluid index ---*/
11302  long *Buffer_Send_SetIndex = NULL;
11303  long *Buffer_Recv_SetIndex = new long[nBuffer_SetIndex];
11304 
11305  /*--- Prepare the receive buffers (1st step) and send buffers (2nd step) on the master node only. ---*/
11306 
11307  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
11308  Buffer_Recv_StructCoord = new su2double[size*nBuffer_StructCoord];
11309  Buffer_Recv_DonorIndices = new long[size*nBuffer_DonorIndices];
11310  Buffer_Send_FlowNewCoord = new su2double[size*nBuffer_FlowNewCoord];
11311  Buffer_Send_SetIndex = new long[size*nBuffer_SetIndex];
11312  }
11313 
11314  /*--- On the structural side ---*/
11315 
11316  /*--- If this processor owns the marker we are looping at on the structural side ---*/
11317 
11318  /*--- First we initialize all of the indices and processors to -1 ---*/
11319  /*--- This helps on identifying halo nodes and avoids setting wrong values ---*/
11320  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nBuffer_DonorIndices; iVertex++)
11321  Buffer_Send_DonorIndices[iVertex] = -1;
11322 
11323  if (Marker_Struct >= 0){
11324 
11325  /*--- We have identified the local index of the FEA marker ---*/
11326  /*--- We loop over all the vertices in that marker and in that particular processor ---*/
11327 
11328  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nLocalVertexStruct; iVertex++){
11329 
11330  Point_Struct = fea_geometry[MESH_0]->vertex[Marker_Struct][iVertex]->GetNode();
11331 
11332  Point_Flow = fea_geometry[MESH_0]->vertex[Marker_Struct][iVertex]->GetDonorPoint();
11333 
11334  Processor_Flow = fea_geometry[MESH_0]->vertex[Marker_Struct][iVertex]->GetDonorProcessor();
11335 
11336  Coord_Struct = fea_geometry[MESH_0]->node[Point_Struct]->GetCoord();
11337 
11338  /*--- The displacements come from the predicted solution ---*/
11339  Displacement_Struct = fea_solution[MESH_0][FEA_SOL]->node[Point_Struct]->GetSolution_Pred();
11340 
11341  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++){
11342  Buffer_Send_StructCoord[iVertex*nDim+iDim] = Coord_Struct[iDim] + Displacement_Struct[iDim];
11343  }
11344  /*--- If this processor owns the node ---*/
11345  if (fea_geometry[MESH_0]->node[Point_Struct]->GetDomain()){
11346  Buffer_Send_DonorIndices[2*iVertex] = Point_Flow;
11347  Buffer_Send_DonorIndices[2*iVertex + 1] = Processor_Flow;
11348  }
11349  else{
11350  /*--- We set the values to be -1 to be able to identify them later as halo nodes ---*/
11351  Buffer_Send_DonorIndices[2*iVertex] = -1;
11352  Buffer_Send_DonorIndices[2*iVertex + 1] = -1;
11353  }
11354 
11355  }
11356  }
11357 
11358  /*--- Once all the messages have been sent, we gather them all into the MASTER_NODE ---*/
11359  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_StructCoord, nBuffer_StructCoord, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Recv_StructCoord, nBuffer_StructCoord, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
11360  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_DonorIndices, nBuffer_DonorIndices, MPI_LONG, Buffer_Recv_DonorIndices, nBuffer_DonorIndices, MPI_LONG, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
11361 
11362  /*--- Counter to determine where in the array we have to set the information ---*/
11363  long *Counter_Processor_Flow = NULL;
11364  long iProcessor_Struct = 0, iIndex_Struct = 0;
11365  long iProcessor_Flow = 0, iPoint_Flow = 0, iIndex_Flow = 0;
11366 
11367  /*--- Now we pack the information to send it over to the different processors ---*/
11368 
11369  if (rank == MASTER_NODE){
11370 
11371  /*--- We set the counter to 0 ---*/
11372  Counter_Processor_Flow = new long[nProcessor];
11373  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < nProcessor; iProcessor++){
11374  Counter_Processor_Flow[iProcessor] = 0;
11375  }
11376 
11377  /*--- First we initialize the index vector to -1 ---*/
11378  /*--- This helps on identifying halo nodes and avoids setting wrong values ---*/
11379  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nProcessor*nBuffer_SetIndex; iVertex++)
11380  Buffer_Send_SetIndex[iVertex] = -2;
11381 
11382  /*--- As of now we do the loop over the structural points ---*/
11383  /*--- The number of points for flow and structure does not necessarily have to match ---*/
11384  /*--- In fact, it's possible that a processor asks for nFlow nodes and there are only ---*/
11385  /*--- nStruc < nFlow available; this is due to halo nodes ---*/
11386 
11387  /*--- For every processor from which we have received information ---*/
11388  /*--- (This is, for every processor on the structural side) ---*/
11389  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < nProcessor; iProcessor++){
11390 
11391  /*--- This is the initial index on the coordinates buffer for that particular processor on the structural side ---*/
11392  iProcessor_Struct = iProcessor*nBuffer_StructCoord;
11393  /*--- This is the initial index on the donor index/processor buffer for that particular processor on the structural side ---*/
11394  iIndex_Struct = iProcessor*nBuffer_DonorIndices;
11395 
11396  /*--- For every vertex in the information retreived from iProcessor ---*/
11397  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < Buffer_Recv_nVertexStruct[iProcessor]; iVertex++) {
11398 
11399  /*--- The processor and index for the flow are: ---*/
11400  Processor_Flow_Rcv = Buffer_Recv_DonorIndices[iIndex_Struct+iVertex*2+1];
11401  Point_Flow_Rcv = Buffer_Recv_DonorIndices[iIndex_Struct+iVertex*2];
11402 
11403  /*--- Load the buffer at the appropriate position ---*/
11404  /*--- This is determined on the fluid side by:
11405  *--- Processor_Flow*nBuffer_FlowNewCoord -> Initial position of the processor array (fluid side)
11406  *--- +
11407  *--- Counter_Processor_Flow*nDim -> Initial position of the nDim array for the particular point on the fluid side
11408  *--- +
11409  *--- iDim -> Position within the nDim array that corresponds to a point
11410  *---
11411  *--- While on the structural side is:
11412  *--- iProcessor*nBuffer_StructCoord -> Initial position on the processor array (structural side)
11413  *--- +
11414  *--- iVertex*nDim -> Initial position of the nDim array for the particular point on the structural side
11415  */
11416 
11417  /*--- We check that we are not setting the value for a halo node ---*/
11418  if (Point_Flow_Rcv != -1){
11419  iProcessor_Flow = Processor_Flow_Rcv*nBuffer_FlowNewCoord;
11420  iIndex_Flow = Processor_Flow_Rcv*nBuffer_SetIndex;
11421  iPoint_Flow = Counter_Processor_Flow[Processor_Flow_Rcv]*nDim;
11422 
11423  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
11424  Buffer_Send_FlowNewCoord[iProcessor_Flow + iPoint_Flow + iDim] = Buffer_Recv_StructCoord[iProcessor_Struct + iVertex*nDim + iDim];
11425 
11426  /*--- We set the fluid index at an appropriate position matching the coordinates ---*/
11427  Buffer_Send_SetIndex[iIndex_Flow + Counter_Processor_Flow[Processor_Flow_Rcv]] = Point_Flow_Rcv;
11428 
11429  Counter_Processor_Flow[Processor_Flow_Rcv]++;
11430  }
11431 
11432  }
11433 
11434  }
11435 
11436  }
11437 
11438  /*--- Once all the messages have been prepared, we scatter them all from the MASTER_NODE ---*/
11439  SU2_MPI::Scatter(Buffer_Send_FlowNewCoord, nBuffer_FlowNewCoord, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Recv_FlowNewCoord, nBuffer_FlowNewCoord, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
11440  SU2_MPI::Scatter(Buffer_Send_SetIndex, nBuffer_SetIndex, MPI_LONG, Buffer_Recv_SetIndex, nBuffer_SetIndex, MPI_LONG, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
11441 
11442  long indexPoint_iVertex, Point_Flow_Check;
11443 
11444  /*--- For the flow marker we are studying ---*/
11445  if (Marker_Flow >= 0){
11446 
11447  /*--- We have identified the local index of the Flow marker ---*/
11448  /*--- We loop over all the vertices in that marker and in that particular processor ---*/
11449 
11450  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nLocalVertexFlow; iVertex++){
11451 
11452  Point_Flow = flow_geometry[MESH_0]->vertex[Marker_Flow][iVertex]->GetNode();
11453 
11454  if (flow_geometry[MESH_0]->node[Point_Flow]->GetDomain()){
11455  /*--- Find the index of the point Point_Flow in the buffer Buffer_Recv_SetIndex ---*/
11456  indexPoint_iVertex = std::distance(Buffer_Recv_SetIndex, std::find(Buffer_Recv_SetIndex, Buffer_Recv_SetIndex + MaxLocalVertexFlow, Point_Flow));
11457 
11458  Point_Flow_Check = Buffer_Recv_SetIndex[indexPoint_iVertex];
11459 
11460  if (Point_Flow_Check < 0) {
11461  cout << "WARNING: A nonphysical point is being considered for mesh deformation." << endl;
11462  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
11463  }
11464 
11465  Coord = flow_geometry[MESH_0]->node[Point_Flow]->GetCoord();
11466 
11467  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
11468  VarCoord[iDim] = (Buffer_Recv_FlowNewCoord[indexPoint_iVertex*nDim+iDim])-Coord[iDim];
11469 
11470  flow_geometry[MESH_0]->vertex[Marker_Flow][iVertex]->SetVarCoord(VarCoord);
11471 
11472  }
11473 
11474  }
11475 
11476  }
11477 
11478  delete [] Buffer_Send_StructCoord;
11479  delete [] Buffer_Send_DonorIndices;
11480  delete [] Buffer_Recv_FlowNewCoord;
11481  delete [] Buffer_Recv_SetIndex;
11482 
11483  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
11484  delete [] Buffer_Recv_nVertexStruct;
11485  delete [] Buffer_Recv_nVertexFlow;
11486  delete [] Buffer_Recv_StructCoord;
11487  delete [] Buffer_Recv_DonorIndices;
11488  delete [] Buffer_Send_FlowNewCoord;
11489  delete [] Buffer_Send_SetIndex;
11490  delete [] Counter_Processor_Flow;
11491  }
11492 
11493 
11494  }
11495 
11496  #endif
11497 
11498  flow_grid_movement->SetVolume_Deformation(flow_geometry[MESH_0], flow_config, true);
11499 
11500 }
11501 
11502 void CEulerSolver::SetFlow_Displacement_Int(CGeometry **flow_geometry, CVolumetricMovement *flow_grid_movement,
11503  CConfig *flow_config, CConfig *fea_config, CGeometry **fea_geometry, CSolver ***fea_solution) {
11504  unsigned short iMarker, iDim, iDonor, nDonor;
11505  unsigned long iVertex;
11506  su2double VarCoord[3];
11507 
11508  unsigned long iPoint_Donor;
11509  su2double *DisplacementDonor, *DisplacementDonor_Prev, coeff;
11510 
11511  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < flow_config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
11512 
11513  if (flow_config->GetMarker_All_FSIinterface(iMarker) != 0) {
11514 
11515  for(iVertex = 0; iVertex < flow_geometry[MESH_0]->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
11516 
11517  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
11518  VarCoord[iDim]=0.0;
11519 
11520  nDonor = flow_geometry[MESH_0]->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetnDonorPoints();
11521 
11522  for (iDonor = 0; iDonor < nDonor; iDonor++){
11523  iPoint_Donor = flow_geometry[MESH_0]->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetInterpDonorPoint(iDonor);
11524  coeff = flow_geometry[MESH_0]->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetDonorCoeff(iDonor);
11525 
11526  /*--- The displacements come from the predicted solution ---*/
11527  DisplacementDonor = fea_solution[MESH_0][FEA_SOL]->node[iPoint_Donor]->GetSolution_Pred();
11528 
11529  DisplacementDonor_Prev = fea_solution[MESH_0][FEA_SOL]->node[iPoint_Donor]->GetSolution_Pred_Old();
11530 
11531  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
11532 
11533  VarCoord[iDim] += (DisplacementDonor[iDim] - DisplacementDonor_Prev[iDim])*coeff;
11534  }
11535 
11536  flow_geometry[MESH_0]->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->SetVarCoord(VarCoord);
11537  }
11538  }
11539  }
11540  flow_grid_movement->SetVolume_Deformation(flow_geometry[MESH_0], flow_config, true);
11541 
11542 }
11543 
11544 void CEulerSolver::LoadRestart(CGeometry **geometry, CSolver ***solver, CConfig *config, int val_iter) {
11545 
11546  /*--- Restart the solution from file information ---*/
11547  unsigned short iDim, iVar, iMesh, iMeshFine;
11548  unsigned long iPoint, index, iChildren, Point_Fine;
11549  unsigned short turb_model = config->GetKind_Turb_Model();
11550  su2double Area_Children, Area_Parent, *Coord, *Solution_Fine, dull_val;
11551  bool compressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == COMPRESSIBLE);
11552  bool incompressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == INCOMPRESSIBLE);
11553  bool freesurface = (config->GetKind_Regime() == FREESURFACE);
11554  bool grid_movement = config->GetGrid_Movement();
11555  bool dual_time = ((config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_1ST) ||
11556  (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_2ND));
11557  bool steady_restart = config->GetSteadyRestart();
11558  bool time_stepping = config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == TIME_STEPPING;
11559  string UnstExt, text_line;
11560  ifstream restart_file;
11561 
11562  unsigned short iZone = config->GetiZone();
11563  unsigned short nZone = geometry[iZone]->GetnZone();
11564 
11565  string restart_filename = config->GetSolution_FlowFileName();
11566 
11567  Coord = new su2double [nDim];
11568  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
11569  Coord[iDim] = 0.0;
11570 
11571  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
11572 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
11573  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
11574 #endif
11575 
11576  /*--- Multizone problems require the number of the zone to be appended. ---*/
11577 
11578  if (nZone > 1)
11579  restart_filename = config->GetMultizone_FileName(restart_filename, iZone);
11580 
11581  /*--- Modify file name for an unsteady restart ---*/
11582 
11583  if (dual_time || time_stepping)
11584  restart_filename = config->GetUnsteady_FileName(restart_filename, val_iter);
11585 
11586  /*--- Open the restart file, and throw an error if this fails. ---*/
11587 
11588  restart_file.open(restart_filename.data(), ios::in);
11589  if (restart_file.fail()) {
11590  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
11591  cout << "There is no flow restart file!! " << restart_filename.data() << "."<< endl;
11592  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
11593  }
11594 
11595  /*--- In case this is a parallel simulation, we need to perform the
11596  Global2Local index transformation first. ---*/
11597 
11598  long *Global2Local = NULL;
11599  Global2Local = new long[geometry[MESH_0]->GetGlobal_nPointDomain()];
11600  /*--- First, set all indices to a negative value by default ---*/
11601  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry[MESH_0]->GetGlobal_nPointDomain(); iPoint++) {
11602  Global2Local[iPoint] = -1;
11603  }
11604 
11605  /*--- Now fill array with the transform values only for local points ---*/
11606 
11607  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry[MESH_0]->GetnPointDomain(); iPoint++) {
11608  Global2Local[geometry[MESH_0]->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex()] = iPoint;
11609  }
11610 
11611  /*--- Read all lines in the restart file ---*/
11612 
11613  long iPoint_Local = 0; unsigned long iPoint_Global = 0;
11614 
11615  /*--- The first line is the header ---*/
11616 
11617  getline (restart_file, text_line);
11618 
11619  while (getline (restart_file, text_line)) {
11620  istringstream point_line(text_line);
11621 
11622  /*--- Retrieve local index. If this node from the restart file lives
11623  on a different processor, the value of iPoint_Local will be -1, as
11624  initialized above. Otherwise, the local index for this node on the
11625  current processor will be returned and used to instantiate the vars. ---*/
11626 
11627  iPoint_Local = Global2Local[iPoint_Global];
11628  if (iPoint_Local >= 0) {
11629 
11630  if (compressible) {
11631  if (nDim == 2) point_line >> index >> Coord[0] >> Coord[1] >> Solution[0] >> Solution[1] >> Solution[2] >> Solution[3];
11632  if (nDim == 3) point_line >> index >> Coord[0] >> Coord[1] >> Coord[2] >> Solution[0] >> Solution[1] >> Solution[2] >> Solution[3] >> Solution[4];
11633  }
11634  if (incompressible) {
11635  if (nDim == 2) point_line >> index >> Coord[0] >> Coord[1] >> Solution[0] >> Solution[1] >> Solution[2];
11636  if (nDim == 3) point_line >> index >> Coord[0] >> Coord[1] >> Coord[2] >> Solution[0] >> Solution[1] >> Solution[2] >> Solution[3];
11637  }
11638  if (freesurface) {
11639  if (nDim == 2) point_line >> index >> Coord[0] >> Coord[1] >> Solution[0] >> Solution[1] >> Solution[2] >> Solution[3];
11640  if (nDim == 3) point_line >> index >> Coord[0] >> Coord[1] >> Coord[2] >> Solution[0] >> Solution[1] >> Solution[2] >> Solution[3] >> Solution[4];
11641  }
11642 
11643  node[iPoint_Local]->SetSolution(Solution);
11644 
11645  /*--- For dynamic meshes, read in and store the
11646  grid coordinates and grid velocities for each node. ---*/
11647 
11648  if (grid_movement) {
11649 
11650  /*--- First, remove any variables for the turbulence model that
11651  appear in the restart file before the grid velocities. ---*/
11652 
11653  if (turb_model == SA || turb_model == SA_NEG) {
11654  point_line >> dull_val;
11655  } else if (turb_model == SST) {
11656  point_line >> dull_val >> dull_val;
11657  }
11658 
11659  /*--- Read in the next 2 or 3 variables which are the grid velocities ---*/
11660  /*--- If we are restarting the solution from a previously computed static calculation (no grid movement) ---*/
11661  /*--- the grid velocities are set to 0. This is useful for FSI computations ---*/
11662 
11663  su2double GridVel[3] = {0.0,0.0,0.0};
11664  if (!steady_restart){
11665  if (nDim == 2) point_line >> GridVel[0] >> GridVel[1];
11666  else point_line >> GridVel[0] >> GridVel[1] >> GridVel[2];
11667  }
11668 
11669 
11670  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
11671  geometry[MESH_0]->node[iPoint_Local]->SetCoord(iDim, Coord[iDim]);
11672  geometry[MESH_0]->node[iPoint_Local]->SetGridVel(iDim, GridVel[iDim]);
11673  }
11674 
11675  }
11676 
11677  }
11678  iPoint_Global++;
11679  }
11680 
11681  /*--- Close the restart file ---*/
11682 
11683  restart_file.close();
11684 
11685  /*--- Free memory needed for the transformation ---*/
11686 
11687  delete [] Global2Local;
11688 
11689  /*--- MPI solution ---*/
11690 
11691  solver[MESH_0][FLOW_SOL]->Set_MPI_Solution(geometry[MESH_0], config);
11692 
11693  /*--- Interpolate the solution down to the coarse multigrid levels ---*/
11694 
11695  for (iMesh = 1; iMesh <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++) {
11696  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry[iMesh]->GetnPoint(); iPoint++) {
11697  Area_Parent = geometry[iMesh]->node[iPoint]->GetVolume();
11698  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Solution[iVar] = 0.0;
11699  for (iChildren = 0; iChildren < geometry[iMesh]->node[iPoint]->GetnChildren_CV(); iChildren++) {
11700  Point_Fine = geometry[iMesh]->node[iPoint]->GetChildren_CV(iChildren);
11701  Area_Children = geometry[iMesh-1]->node[Point_Fine]->GetVolume();
11702  Solution_Fine = solver[iMesh-1][FLOW_SOL]->node[Point_Fine]->GetSolution();
11703  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
11704  Solution[iVar] += Solution_Fine[iVar]*Area_Children/Area_Parent;
11705  }
11706  }
11707  solver[iMesh][FLOW_SOL]->node[iPoint]->SetSolution(Solution);
11708  }
11709  solver[iMesh][FLOW_SOL]->Set_MPI_Solution(geometry[iMesh], config);
11710  }
11711 
11712  /*--- Update the geometry for flows on dynamic meshes ---*/
11713 
11714  if (grid_movement) {
11715 
11716  /*--- Communicate the new coordinates and grid velocities at the halos ---*/
11717 
11718  geometry[MESH_0]->Set_MPI_Coord(config);
11719  geometry[MESH_0]->Set_MPI_GridVel(config);
11720 
11721  /*--- Recompute the edges and dual mesh control volumes in the
11722  domain and on the boundaries. ---*/
11723 
11724  geometry[MESH_0]->SetCoord_CG();
11725  geometry[MESH_0]->SetControlVolume(config, UPDATE);
11726  geometry[MESH_0]->SetBoundControlVolume(config, UPDATE);
11727 
11728  /*--- Update the multigrid structure after setting up the finest grid,
11729  including computing the grid velocities on the coarser levels. ---*/
11730 
11731  for (iMesh = 1; iMesh <= config->GetnMGLevels(); iMesh++) {
11732  iMeshFine = iMesh-1;
11733  geometry[iMesh]->SetControlVolume(config, geometry[iMeshFine], UPDATE);
11734  geometry[iMesh]->SetBoundControlVolume(config, geometry[iMeshFine],UPDATE);
11735  geometry[iMesh]->SetCoord(geometry[iMeshFine]);
11736  geometry[iMesh]->SetRestricted_GridVelocity(geometry[iMeshFine], config);
11737  }
11738  }
11739 
11740  delete [] Coord;
11741 
11742 }
11743 
11744 void CEulerSolver::SetFreeSurface_Distance(CGeometry *geometry, CConfig *config) {
11745  su2double *coord = NULL, dist2, *iCoord = NULL, *jCoord = NULL, LevelSet_i, LevelSet_j,
11746  **Coord_LevelSet = NULL, *xCoord = NULL, *yCoord = NULL, *zCoord = NULL, auxCoordx, auxCoordy,
11747  auxCoordz, FreeSurface, volume, LevelSetDiff_Squared, LevelSetDiff, dist, Min_dist;
11748  unsigned short iDim;
11749  unsigned long iPoint, jPoint, iVertex, jVertex, nVertex_LevelSet, iEdge;
11750  ifstream index_file;
11751  ofstream LevelSet_file;
11752  string text_line;
11753  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
11754  char cstr[200], buffer[50];
11755 
11756  unsigned short nDim = geometry->GetnDim();
11757  unsigned long iExtIter = config->GetExtIter();
11758 
11759 #ifndef HAVE_MPI
11760 
11761  /*--- Identification of the 0 level set points and coordinates ---*/
11762  nVertex_LevelSet = 0;
11763  for (iEdge = 0; iEdge < geometry->GetnEdge(); iEdge++) {
11764  iPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(0); LevelSet_i = node[iPoint]->GetSolution(nDim+1);
11765  jPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(1); LevelSet_j = node[jPoint]->GetSolution(nDim+1);
11766  if (LevelSet_i*LevelSet_j < 0.0) nVertex_LevelSet ++;
11767  }
11768 
11769  /*--- Allocate vector of boundary coordinates ---*/
11770  Coord_LevelSet = new su2double* [nVertex_LevelSet];
11771  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nVertex_LevelSet; iVertex++)
11772  Coord_LevelSet[iVertex] = new su2double [nDim];
11773 
11774  /*--- Get coordinates of the points of the surface ---*/
11775  nVertex_LevelSet = 0;
11776  for (iEdge = 0; iEdge < geometry->GetnEdge(); iEdge++) {
11777  iPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(0); LevelSet_i = node[iPoint]->GetSolution(nDim+1); iCoord = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord();
11778  jPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(1); LevelSet_j = node[jPoint]->GetSolution(nDim+1); jCoord = geometry->node[jPoint]->GetCoord();
11779  if (LevelSet_i*LevelSet_j < 0.0) {
11780  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
11781  Coord_LevelSet[nVertex_LevelSet][iDim] = iCoord[iDim]-LevelSet_i*(jCoord[iDim]-iCoord[iDim])/(LevelSet_j-LevelSet_i);
11782  nVertex_LevelSet++;
11783  }
11784  }
11785 
11786 #else
11787 
11788  int nProcessor, iProcessor;
11789  unsigned long *Buffer_Send_nVertex = NULL, *Buffer_Receive_nVertex = NULL,
11790  nLocalVertex_LevelSet = 0, nGlobalVertex_LevelSet = 0, MaxLocalVertex_LevelSet = 0, nBuffer;
11791  su2double *Buffer_Send_Coord = NULL, *Buffer_Receive_Coord = NULL;
11792 
11793  MPI_Comm_size(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &nProcessor);
11794  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
11795 
11796  Buffer_Send_nVertex = new unsigned long [1];
11797  Buffer_Receive_nVertex = new unsigned long [nProcessor];
11798 
11799  nLocalVertex_LevelSet = 0;
11800  for (iEdge = 0; iEdge < geometry->GetnEdge(); iEdge++) {
11801  iPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(0); LevelSet_i = node[iPoint]->GetSolution(nDim+1);
11802  jPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(1); LevelSet_j = node[jPoint]->GetSolution(nDim+1);
11803  if (LevelSet_i*LevelSet_j < 0.0) nLocalVertex_LevelSet ++;
11804  }
11805 
11806  Buffer_Send_nVertex[0] = nLocalVertex_LevelSet;
11807 
11808  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&nLocalVertex_LevelSet, &nGlobalVertex_LevelSet, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MPI_SUM, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
11809  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&nLocalVertex_LevelSet, &MaxLocalVertex_LevelSet, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MPI_MAX, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
11810  SU2_MPI::Allgather(Buffer_Send_nVertex, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, Buffer_Receive_nVertex, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
11811 
11812  nBuffer = MaxLocalVertex_LevelSet*nDim;
11813  Buffer_Send_Coord = new su2double [nBuffer];
11814  Buffer_Receive_Coord = new su2double [nProcessor*nBuffer];
11815 
11816  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < MaxLocalVertex_LevelSet; iVertex++)
11817  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
11818  Buffer_Send_Coord[iVertex*nDim+iDim] = 0.0;
11819 
11820  nLocalVertex_LevelSet = 0;
11821  for (iEdge = 0; iEdge < geometry->GetnEdge(); iEdge++) {
11822  iPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(0); LevelSet_i = node[iPoint]->GetSolution(nDim+1); iCoord = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord();
11823  jPoint = geometry->edge[iEdge]->GetNode(1); LevelSet_j = node[jPoint]->GetSolution(nDim+1); jCoord = geometry->node[jPoint]->GetCoord();
11824 
11825  if (LevelSet_i*LevelSet_j < 0.0) {
11826  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
11827  Buffer_Send_Coord[nLocalVertex_LevelSet*nDim+iDim] = iCoord[iDim]-LevelSet_i*(jCoord[iDim]-iCoord[iDim])/(LevelSet_j-LevelSet_i);
11828  nLocalVertex_LevelSet++;
11829  }
11830  }
11831 
11832  SU2_MPI::Allgather(Buffer_Send_Coord, nBuffer, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Receive_Coord, nBuffer, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
11833 
11834  /*--- Identification of the 0 level set points and coordinates ---*/
11835  nVertex_LevelSet = 0;
11836  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < nProcessor; iProcessor++)
11837  nVertex_LevelSet += Buffer_Receive_nVertex[iProcessor];
11838 
11839  /*--- Allocate vector of boundary coordinates ---*/
11840  Coord_LevelSet = new su2double* [nVertex_LevelSet];
11841  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nVertex_LevelSet; iVertex++)
11842  Coord_LevelSet[iVertex] = new su2double [nDim];
11843 
11844  /*--- Set the value of the coordinates at the level set zero ---*/
11845  nVertex_LevelSet = 0;
11846  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < nProcessor; iProcessor++)
11847  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < Buffer_Receive_nVertex[iProcessor]; iVertex++) {
11848  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
11849  Coord_LevelSet[nVertex_LevelSet][iDim] = Buffer_Receive_Coord[(iProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_LevelSet+iVertex)*nDim+iDim];
11850  nVertex_LevelSet++;
11851  }
11852 
11853  delete [] Buffer_Send_Coord;
11854  delete [] Buffer_Receive_Coord;
11855  delete [] Buffer_Send_nVertex;
11856  delete [] Buffer_Receive_nVertex;
11857 
11858 #endif
11859 
11860  /*--- Get coordinates of the points and compute distances to the surface ---*/
11861  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPoint; iPoint++) {
11862  coord = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord();
11863 
11864  /*--- Compute the min distance ---*/
11865  Min_dist = 1E20;
11866  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nVertex_LevelSet; iVertex++) {
11867 
11868  dist2 = 0.0;
11869  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
11870  dist2 += (coord[iDim] - Coord_LevelSet[iVertex][iDim])*(coord[iDim]-Coord_LevelSet[iVertex][iDim]);
11871  dist = sqrt(dist2);
11872  if (dist < Min_dist) { Min_dist = dist; }
11873 
11874  }
11875 
11876  /*--- Compute the sign using the current solution ---*/
11877  su2double NumberSign = 1.0;
11878  if (node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0) != 0.0)
11879  NumberSign = node[iPoint]->GetSolution(nDim+1)/fabs(node[iPoint]->GetSolution(nDim+1));
11880 
11881  /*--- Store the value of the Level Set and the Distance (primitive variables) ---*/
11882  node[iPoint]->SetPrimitive(nDim+5, node[iPoint]->GetSolution(nDim+1));
11883  node[iPoint]->SetPrimitive(nDim+6, Min_dist*NumberSign);
11884 
11885  }
11886 
11887  if (config->GetIntIter() == 0) {
11888 
11889  /*--- Order the arrays (x Coordinate, y Coordinate, z Coordiante) ---*/
11890  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nVertex_LevelSet; iVertex++) {
11891  for (jVertex = 0; jVertex < nVertex_LevelSet - 1 - iVertex; jVertex++) {
11892  if (Coord_LevelSet[jVertex][0] > Coord_LevelSet[jVertex+1][0]) {
11893  auxCoordx = Coord_LevelSet[jVertex][0]; Coord_LevelSet[jVertex][0] = Coord_LevelSet[jVertex+1][0]; Coord_LevelSet[jVertex+1][0] = auxCoordx;
11894  auxCoordy = Coord_LevelSet[jVertex][1]; Coord_LevelSet[jVertex][1] = Coord_LevelSet[jVertex+1][1]; Coord_LevelSet[jVertex+1][1] = auxCoordy;
11895  if (nDim == 3) { auxCoordz = Coord_LevelSet[jVertex][2]; Coord_LevelSet[jVertex][2] = Coord_LevelSet[jVertex+1][2]; Coord_LevelSet[jVertex+1][2] = auxCoordz; }
11896  }
11897  }
11898  }
11899 
11900  /*--- Get coordinates of the points and compute distances to the surface ---*/
11901  FreeSurface = 0.0;
11902  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPointDomain; iPoint++) {
11903  coord = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord();
11904  volume = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetVolume();
11905  LevelSetDiff = (node[iPoint]->GetSolution(nDim+1) - coord[nDim-1]);
11906  LevelSetDiff_Squared = LevelSetDiff*LevelSetDiff;
11907  FreeSurface += 0.5*LevelSetDiff_Squared*volume;
11908 
11909  node[iPoint]->SetDiffLevelSet(LevelSetDiff);
11910 
11911  }
11912 
11913  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (iExtIter % config->GetWrt_Sol_Freq_DualTime() == 0)) {
11914 
11915  /*--- Write the Level Set distribution, the target level set---*/
11916  LevelSet_file.precision(15);
11917 
11918  /*--- Write file name with extension ---*/
11919  strcpy (cstr, "LevelSet");
11920  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation()) {
11921  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 0) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 10)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0000%d.dat", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
11922  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 10) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 100)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_000%d.dat", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
11923  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 100) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 1000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_00%d.dat", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
11924  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 1000) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 10000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0%d.dat", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
11925  if (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 10000) SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d.dat", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
11926  }
11927  else {
11928  SPRINTF (buffer, ".dat");
11929  }
11930 
11931  strcat(cstr, buffer);
11932 
11933  LevelSet_file.open(cstr, ios::out);
11934  LevelSet_file << "TITLE = \"SU2 Free surface simulation\"" << endl;
11935  if (nDim == 2) LevelSet_file << "VARIABLES = \"x coord\",\"y coord\"" << endl;
11936  if (nDim == 3) LevelSet_file << "VARIABLES = \"x coord\",\"y coord\",\"z coord\"" << endl;
11937  LevelSet_file << "ZONE T= \"Free Surface\"" << endl;
11938 
11939  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nVertex_LevelSet; iVertex++) {
11940  if (nDim == 2) LevelSet_file << scientific << Coord_LevelSet[iVertex][0] << ", " << Coord_LevelSet[iVertex][1] << endl;
11941  if (nDim == 3) LevelSet_file << scientific << Coord_LevelSet[iVertex][0] << ", " << Coord_LevelSet[iVertex][1] << ", " << Coord_LevelSet[iVertex][2] << endl;
11942  }
11943  LevelSet_file.close();
11944 
11945  }
11946 
11947  /*--- Store the value of the free surface coefficient ---*/
11948  SetTotal_CFreeSurface(FreeSurface);
11949 
11950  delete [] xCoord;
11951  delete [] yCoord;
11952  if (nDim == 3) delete [] zCoord;
11953 
11954  }
11955 
11956  /*--- Deallocate vector of boundary coordinates ---*/
11957  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < nVertex_LevelSet; iVertex++)
11958  delete Coord_LevelSet[iVertex];
11959  delete [] Coord_LevelSet;
11960 
11961 }

11963 void CEulerSolver::SetFreeStream_Solution(CConfig *config){
11964 
11965  bool compressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == COMPRESSIBLE);
11966  bool incompressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == INCOMPRESSIBLE);
11967  unsigned long iPoint;
11968  unsigned short iDim;
11969 
11970  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPoint; iPoint++){
11971 
11972  if (compressible){
11973  node[iPoint]->SetSolution(0, Density_Inf);
11974  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++){
11975  node[iPoint]->SetSolution(iDim+1, Density_Inf*Velocity_Inf[iDim]);
11976  }
11977  node[iPoint]->SetSolution(nVar-1, Density_Inf*Energy_Inf);
11978  }
11979  if (incompressible){
11980  node[iPoint]->SetSolution(0, Pressure_Inf);
11981  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++){
11982  node[iPoint]->SetSolution(iDim+1, Density_Inf*Velocity_Inf[iDim]);
11983  }
11984  }
11985  }
11986 }

12010 CNSSolver::CNSSolver(CGeometry *geometry, CConfig *config, unsigned short iMesh) : CEulerSolver() {

12016  ifstream restart_file;

12018  unsigned short nZone = geometry->GetnZone();
12019  bool restart = (config->GetRestart() || config->GetRestart_Flow());
12020  bool compressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == COMPRESSIBLE);
12021  bool incompressible = (config->GetKind_Regime() == INCOMPRESSIBLE);
12022  bool freesurface = (config->GetKind_Regime() == FREESURFACE);
12023  bool dual_time = ((config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_1ST) ||
12024  (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == DT_STEPPING_2ND));

12028  string filename = config->GetSolution_FlowFileName();
12029 
12030  unsigned short direct_diff = config->GetDirectDiff();
12031  unsigned short nMarkerTurboPerf = config->Get_nMarkerTurboPerf();
12032 
12033  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
12034 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
12035  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
12036 #endif
12037 
12038  /*--- Array initialization ---*/
12039 
12040  CDrag_Visc = NULL; CLift_Visc = NULL; CSideForce_Visc = NULL; CEff_Visc = NULL;
12041  CMx_Visc = NULL; CMy_Visc = NULL; CMz_Visc = NULL;
12042  CFx_Visc = NULL; CFy_Visc = NULL; CFz_Visc = NULL;
12043 
12044  Surface_CLift_Visc = NULL; Surface_CDrag_Visc = NULL; Surface_CSideForce_Visc = NULL; Surface_CEff_Visc = NULL;
12045  Surface_CFx_Visc = NULL; Surface_CFy_Visc = NULL; Surface_CFz_Visc = NULL;
12046  Surface_CMx_Visc = NULL; Surface_CMy_Visc = NULL; Surface_CMz_Visc = NULL;
12047

12049  MaxHeatFlux_Visc = NULL; ForceViscous = NULL; MomentViscous = NULL;
12050  CSkinFriction = NULL; Cauchy_Serie = NULL; Heat_Visc = NULL;
12051 
12052  /*--- Set the gamma value ---*/
12053 
12054  Gamma = config->GetGamma();
12055  Gamma_Minus_One = Gamma - 1.0;
12056 
12057  /*--- Define geometry constants in the solver structure
12058  Compressible flow, primitive variables (T, vx, vy, vz, P, rho, h, c, lamMu, EddyMu, ThCond, Cp)
12059  Incompressible flow, primitive variables (P, vx, vy, vz, rho, beta, lamMu, EddyMu),
12060  FreeSurface Incompressible flow, primitive variables (P, vx, vy, vz, rho, beta, lamMu, EddyMu, LevelSet, Dist),
12061  ---*/
12062 
12063  nDim = geometry->GetnDim();
12064 
12065  if (incompressible) { nVar = nDim+1; nPrimVar = nDim+5; nPrimVarGrad = nDim+3; }
12066  if (freesurface) { nVar = nDim+2; nPrimVar = nDim+7; nPrimVarGrad = nDim+6; }
12067  if (compressible) { nVar = nDim+2;
12068  nPrimVar = nDim+9; nPrimVarGrad = nDim+4;
12069  nSecondaryVar = 8; nSecondaryVarGrad = 2;
12070  }
12071 
12072  nMarker = config->GetnMarker_All();
12073  nPoint = geometry->GetnPoint();
12074  nPointDomain = geometry->GetnPointDomain();
12075 
12076  /*--- Perform the non-dimensionalization for the flow equations using the
12077  specified reference values. ---*/
12078 
12079  SetNondimensionalization(geometry, config, iMesh);
12080 
12081  /*--- Allocate the node variables ---*/
12082  node = new CVariable*[nPoint];
12083 
12084  /*--- Define some auxiliar vector related with the residual ---*/
12085 
12086  Residual = new su2double[nVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Residual[iVar] = 0.0;
12087  Residual_RMS = new su2double[nVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Residual_RMS[iVar] = 0.0;
12088  Residual_Max = new su2double[nVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Residual_Max[iVar] = 0.0;
12089  Residual_i = new su2double[nVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Residual_i[iVar] = 0.0;
12090  Residual_j = new su2double[nVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Residual_j[iVar] = 0.0;
12091  Res_Conv = new su2double[nVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Res_Conv[iVar] = 0.0;
12092  Res_Visc = new su2double[nVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Res_Visc[iVar] = 0.0;
12093  Res_Sour = new su2double[nVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Res_Sour[iVar] = 0.0;
12094 
12095  /*--- Define some structures for locating max residuals ---*/
12096 
12097  Point_Max = new unsigned long[nVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Point_Max[iVar] = 0;
12098  Point_Max_Coord = new su2double*[nVar];
12099  for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) {
12100  Point_Max_Coord[iVar] = new su2double[nDim];
12101  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Point_Max_Coord[iVar][iDim] = 0.0;
12102  }
12103 
12104  /*--- Define some auxiliary vectors related to the solution ---*/
12105 
12106  Solution = new su2double[nVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Solution[iVar] = 0.0;
12107  Solution_i = new su2double[nVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Solution_i[iVar] = 0.0;
12108  Solution_j = new su2double[nVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nVar; iVar++) Solution_j[iVar] = 0.0;
12109 
12110  /*--- Define some auxiliary vectors related to the geometry ---*/
12111 
12112  Vector = new su2double[nDim]; for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Vector[iDim] = 0.0;
12113  Vector_i = new su2double[nDim]; for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Vector_i[iDim] = 0.0;
12114  Vector_j = new su2double[nDim]; for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) Vector_j[iDim] = 0.0;
12115 
12116  /*--- Define some auxiliary vectors related to the primitive solution ---*/
12117 
12118  Primitive = new su2double[nPrimVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nPrimVar; iVar++) Primitive[iVar] = 0.0;
12119  Primitive_i = new su2double[nPrimVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nPrimVar; iVar++) Primitive_i[iVar] = 0.0;
12120  Primitive_j = new su2double[nPrimVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nPrimVar; iVar++) Primitive_j[iVar] = 0.0;
12121 
12122  /*--- Define some auxiliary vectors related to the Secondary solution ---*/
12123 
12124  if (compressible){
12125  Secondary = new su2double[nSecondaryVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nSecondaryVar; iVar++) Secondary[iVar] = 0.0;
12126  Secondary_i = new su2double[nSecondaryVar]; for (iVar = 0; iVar < nSecondaryVar; iVar++) Secondary_i[iVar] = 0.0;

12576 
12577  /*--- In case this is a parallel simulation, we need to perform the
12578  Global2Local index transformation first. ---*/
12579 
12580  long *Global2Local = new long[geometry->GetGlobal_nPointDomain()];
12581 
12582  /*--- First, set all indices to a negative value by default ---*/
12583 
12584  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry->GetGlobal_nPointDomain(); iPoint++)
12585  Global2Local[iPoint] = -1;
12586 
12587  /*--- Now fill array with the transform values only for local points ---*/
12588 
12589  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPointDomain; iPoint++)
12590  Global2Local[geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex()] = iPoint;
12591 
12592  /*--- Read all lines in the restart file ---*/
12593 
12594  long iPoint_Local;
12595  unsigned long iPoint_Global_Local = 0, iPoint_Global = 0; string text_line;
12596  unsigned short rbuf_NotMatching = 0, sbuf_NotMatching = 0;
12597 
12598  /*--- The first line is the header ---*/
12599 
12600  getline (restart_file, text_line);
12601 
12602  while (getline (restart_file, text_line)) {
12603  istringstream point_line(text_line);
12604 
12605  /*--- Retrieve local index. If this node from the restart file lives
12606  on a different processor, the value of iPoint_Local will be -1.
12607  Otherwise, the local index for this node on the current processor
12608  will be returned and used to instantiate the vars. ---*/
12609 
12610  if (iPoint_Global >= geometry->GetGlobal_nPointDomain()) { sbuf_NotMatching = 1; break; }
12611 
12612  iPoint_Local = Global2Local[iPoint_Global];
12613 
12614  /*--- Load the solution for this node. Note that the first entry
12615  on the restart file line is the global index, followed by the
12616  node coordinates, and then the conservative variables. ---*/
12617 
12618  if (iPoint_Local >= 0) {
12619  if (compressible) {
12620  if (nDim == 2) point_line >> index >> dull_val >> dull_val >> Solution[0] >> Solution[1] >> Solution[2] >> Solution[3];
12621  if (nDim == 3) point_line >> index >> dull_val >> dull_val >> dull_val >> Solution[0] >> Solution[1] >> Solution[2] >> Solution[3] >> Solution[4];
12622  }
12623  if (incompressible) {
12624  if (nDim == 2) point_line >> index >> dull_val >> dull_val >> Solution[0] >> Solution[1] >> Solution[2];
12625  if (nDim == 3) point_line >> index >> dull_val >> dull_val >> dull_val >> Solution[0] >> Solution[1] >> Solution[2] >> Solution[3];
12626  }
12627  if (freesurface) {
12628  if (nDim == 2) point_line >> index >> dull_val >> dull_val >> Solution[0] >> Solution[1] >> Solution[2] >> Solution[3];
12629  if (nDim == 3) point_line >> index >> dull_val >> dull_val >> dull_val >> Solution[0] >> Solution[1] >> Solution[2] >> Solution[3] >> Solution[4];
12630  }
12631  node[iPoint_Local] = new CNSVariable(Solution, nDim, nVar, config);
12632  iPoint_Global_Local++;
12633  }
12634  iPoint_Global++;
12635  }
12636 
12637  /*--- Detect a wrong solution file ---*/
12638 
12639  if (iPoint_Global_Local < nPointDomain) { sbuf_NotMatching = 1; }
12640 
12641 #ifndef HAVE_MPI
12642  rbuf_NotMatching = sbuf_NotMatching;
12643 #else
12644  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&sbuf_NotMatching, &rbuf_NotMatching, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_SHORT, MPI_SUM, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
12645 #endif
12646 
12647  if (rbuf_NotMatching != 0) {
12648  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
12649  cout << endl << "The solution file " << filename.data() << " doesn't match with the mesh file!" << endl;
12650  cout << "It could be empty lines at the end of the file." << endl << endl;
12651  }
12652 #ifndef HAVE_MPI
12653  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
12654 #else
12655  MPI_Barrier(MPI_COMM_WORLD);
12656  MPI_Abort(MPI_COMM_WORLD,1);
12657  MPI_Finalize();
12658 #endif
12659  }
12660 
12661  /*--- Instantiate the variable class with an arbitrary solution
12662  at any halo/periodic nodes. The initial solution can be arbitrary,
12663  because a send/recv is performed immediately in the solver. ---*/
12664 
12665  for (iPoint = nPointDomain; iPoint < nPoint; iPoint++)
12666  node[iPoint] = new CNSVariable(Solution, nDim, nVar, config);
12667 
12668  /*--- Close the restart file ---*/
12669 
12670  restart_file.close();
12671 
12672  /*--- Free memory needed for the transformation ---*/
12673 
12674  delete [] Global2Local;
12675 
12676  }
12677 
12678  /*--- Check that the initial solution is physical, report any non-physical nodes ---*/
12679 
12680  if (compressible) {
12681 
12682  counter_local = 0;
12683 
12684  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPoint; iPoint++) {
12685 
12686  Density = node[iPoint]->GetSolution(0);
12687 
12688  Velocity2 = 0.0;
12689  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
12690  Velocity2 += (node[iPoint]->GetSolution(iDim+1)/Density)*(node[iPoint]->GetSolution(iDim+1)/Density);
12691 
12692  StaticEnergy= node[iPoint]->GetSolution(nDim+1)/Density - 0.5*Velocity2;
12693 
12694  FluidModel->SetTDState_rhoe(Density, StaticEnergy);
12695  Pressure= FluidModel->GetPressure();
12696  Temperature= FluidModel->GetTemperature();
12697 
12698  /*--- Use the values at the infinity ---*/
12699 
12700  if ((Pressure < 0.0) || (Density < 0.0) || (Temperature < 0.0)) {
12701  Solution[0] = Density_Inf;
12702  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
12703  Solution[iDim+1] = Velocity_Inf[iDim]*Density_Inf;
12704  Solution[nDim+1] = Energy_Inf*Density_Inf;
12705  node[iPoint]->SetSolution(Solution);
12706  node[iPoint]->SetSolution_Old(Solution);
12707  counter_local++;
12708  }
12709 
12710  }
12711 
12712  /*--- Warning message about non-physical points ---*/
12713 
12714  if (config->GetConsole_Output_Verb() == VERB_HIGH) {
12715 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
12716  SU2_MPI::Reduce(&counter_local, &counter_global, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MPI_SUM, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
12717 #else
12718  counter_global = counter_local;
12719 #endif
12720  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (counter_global != 0))
12721  cout << "Warning. The original solution contains "<< counter_global << " points that are not physical." << endl;
12722  }
12723 
12724  }
12725 
12726  /*--- For incompressible solver set the initial values for the density and viscosity,
12727  unless a freesurface problem, this must be constant during the computation ---*/
12728 
12729  if (incompressible || freesurface) {
12730  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nPoint; iPoint++) {
12731  node[iPoint]->SetDensityInc(Density_Inf);
12732  node[iPoint]->SetLaminarViscosityInc(Viscosity_Inf);
12733  }
12734  }
12735 
12736  /*--- Define solver parameters needed for execution of destructor ---*/
12737 
12738  if (config->GetKind_ConvNumScheme_Flow() == SPACE_CENTERED) space_centered = true;
12739  else space_centered = false;
12740 
12741  if (config->GetKind_TimeIntScheme_Flow() == EULER_IMPLICIT) euler_implicit = true;
12742  else euler_implicit = false;
12743 
12744  if (config->GetKind_Gradient_Method() == WEIGHTED_LEAST_SQUARES) least_squares = true;
12745  else least_squares = false;
12746 
12747  /*--- Perform the MPI communication of the solution ---*/
12748 
12749  Set_MPI_Solution(geometry, config);
12750 
12751 }
12752
